)@@G@@  *   @]@@@@       ***  @]@@@@      ***** @]@@@@     *******@#@@@@    **VI
)@@G@@*******     @#@@@@   ***********    @#@@@@  *************   @#@@@@ *****VJ
)@@G@@**********  @#@@@@***************** @]@@@@        ^   ___@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@VK
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@VL
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@* ICEBVM
)@@G@@OL    @]@@@@ICEBOL.VER.2@G@@@@******************************************VN
)@@G@@******************************@G@@@@*                                   VO
)@@G@@                                   *@G@@@@*                             VP
)@@G@@                                         *@G@@@@*                       VQ
)@@G@@       ICEBOL                                  *@G@@@@*                 VR
)@@G@@                                                     *@G@@@@*     IS A PVS
)@@G@@ROGRAM TO COMPRESS SNOBOL4 SOURCE PROGRAMS.  IT DOES THIS  *@G@@@@*     VT
)@@G@@BY REPLACING A SEQUENCE OF BLANKS BY A SINGLE BLANK AND IF NEC-  *@G@@@@VU
)@@G@@*     ESSARY INDICATES AN END-OF-STATEMENT WITH A SEMI-COLON.          *VV
)@@G@@@G@@@@*     A TYPICAL COMPRESSION FACTOR IS THREE TO ONE.               VW
)@@G@@     *@G@@@@*                                                           VX
)@@G@@           *@G@@@@*                            USAGE                    VY
)@@G@@                 *@G@@@@*     THE INPUT DATA TO ICEBOL CAN BE ANY SNOBOLVZ
)@@G@@4 PROGRAM OR SECTION OF*@G@@@@*     PROGRAM PRECEDED BY ZERO OR MORE CONWA
)@@G@@TROL CARDS.  CONTROL CARDS   *@G@@@@*     START WITH A VERTICAL LINE IN WB
)@@G@@COLUMN 1, AND MAY BE ANY OF THE    *@G@@@@*     FOLLOWING (WHERE BLANKS WC
)@@G@@ARE IRRELEVENT)                          *@G@@@@*     !   DON'T CRUNCH CWD
)@@G@@OMMENTS                                        *@G@@@@*     !   NO  COMMWE
)@@G@@ENTS                                                 *@G@@@@*     !   NOWF
)@@G@@ LIST                                                      *@G@@@@*     WG
)@@G@@COMMENTS ARE NORMALLY INCLUDED AS PART OF THE COMPRESSED DECK BUT*@G@@@@WH
)@@G@@*     KEEPING WITHIN THE SPIRIT OF ICEBOL SUCCESSIVE BLANKS ARE        *WI
)@@G@@@G@@@@*     NORMALLY REPLACED BY A SINGLE BLANK AND THEREBY MULTI-LINE  WJ
)@@G@@     *@G@@@@*     COMMENTS CAN BE COMPRESSED.  THE FIRST CONTROL CARD   WK
)@@G@@           *@G@@@@*     ABOVE SUPPRESSES THE COMPRESSION OF COMMENTS.  TWL
)@@G@@HE SECOND CONT-  *@G@@@@*     ROL CARD ABOVE REMOVES COMMENTS ALTOGETHERWM
)@@G@@.                      *@G@@@@*     SNOBOL4 CONTROL CARDS (CARDS BEGINNIWN
)@@G@@NG WITH A MINUS , -)  NORMAL-*@G@@@@*     LY APPEAR BY THEMSELVES ON A SWO
)@@G@@INGLE LINE.  THESE WILL BE REMOVED *@G@@@@*     IF THE THIRD CONTROL CARWP
)@@G@@D ABOVE IS INCLUDED.                     *@G@@@@*                       WQ
)@@G@@                                               *@G@@@@*                 WR
)@@G@@    LABELING AND CARD NUMBERING                      *@G@@@@*           WS
)@@G@@                                                           *@G@@@@*     WT
)@@G@@THE FIRST FOUR CHARACTERS OF THE FIRST CARD ARE USED TO LABEL THE*@G@@@@WU
)@@G@@*     DECK.  THE DECK IS SEQUENCE NUMBERED.                            *WV
)@@G@@@G@@@@*                                                                 WW
)@@G@@     *@G@@@@*                                                           WX
)@@G@@           *@G@@@@*                                                     WY
)@@G@@J. F. GIMPEL     *@G@@@@*                                               WZ
)@@G@@      7/15/68          *@G@@@@*                                         XA
)@@G@@                             *@G@@@@*                                   XB
)@@G@@                                   *@G@@@@******************************XC
)@@G@@******************************************@ @[@@         INPUT('INPUT',5XD
)@@G@@,72)  @A@@@[         UNITI  =  IDENT(UNITI)  5  @A@@@[         UNITO  = XE
)@@G@@ IDENT(UNITO)  6  @A@@@[         UNITP  =  IDENT(UNITP)  1  @A@@@[      XF
)@@G@@   INPUT('INPUT',UNITI,72)    @F@@@@         DEFINE( 'BLANK(N)')        XG
)@@G@@             :(BLANK.END)     @E@@@@BLANK    BLANK = DUP(' ',N)         XH
)@@G@@             :(RETURN)  @E@@@@BLANK.END DEFINE('DUP(S,N)')              XI
)@@G@@       :(DUP.END) @E@@@@DUP      DUP = GT(N,0) DUP S                    XJ
)@@G@@ :F(RETURN) @E@@@@         N = N - 1                               :(DUPXK
)@@G@@)     @E@@@@DUP.END  DEFINE( 'RADJ(S,N)')                    :(RADJ.END)XL
)@@G@@@E@@@@RADJ     (MANY.BLANKS S) RTAB(N) REM . RADJ      :S( RETURN)@E@@@@XM
)@@G@@         MANY.BLANKS = MANY.BLANKS '         '   :(RADJ)    @E@@@@RADJ.EXN
)@@G@@ND DEFINE( 'LADJ(S,N)')                    :(LADJ.END)@E@@@@LADJ     (S XO
)@@G@@MANY.BLANKS) TAB(N) . LADJ           :S(RETURN) @E@@@@         MANY.BLANXP
)@@G@@KS = MANY.BLANKS '       '     :(LADJ)    @E@@@@LADJ.END DEFINE('TOSS(A)XQ
)@@G@@')                       :(TOSS.END)@E@@@@TOSS     IDENT(A)             XR
)@@G@@                   :S(RETURN) @ @@@@         CARD.NO = CARD.NO + 1@C@@@@XS
)@@G@@         A = LADJ(A ,72) LABEL RADJ(CARD.NO,4)  @#@@@@         PUNCH = AXT
)@@G@@@#@@@@         OUTPUT = @^@@@@         OUTPUT = A     @E@@@@         OUTXU
)@@G@@PUT =                                :(RETURN)  @F@@@@TOSS.END DEFINE('SXV
)@@G@@PACE(N)')                      :(SPACE.END)     @G@@@@SPACE    N GT(N,0)XW
)@@G@@ . OUTPUT REM = N - 1          :S(SPACE) F(RETURN)    @B@@@@SPACE.END SPXX
)@@G@@ECIAL = FENCE ( '*' ! '-')    @ @@@@         COMMENT = FENCE '*'  @ @@@@XY

)@@G@@T)) . C     @G@@@@         NB72S.PATTERN = (TAB(60) ARB) . N ' ' ARBNO(NAV
)@@G@@OTANY(' ')) . B   @#@@@@.        RPOS(0)  @E@@@@SQ.0     S = CAT.IN()   AW

)@@G@@DED.  @G@@@@************************************************************EE
)@@G@@************@ @@@@FREE STORAGE SIZE CONTROL.    @G@@@@   THE USE OF MCOREF
)@@G@@E$ TO EXPAND THE FREE STORAGE AREA WHEN A PROGRAM     @G@@@@GETS TOO BIGEG
)@@G@@ HAS BEEN IMPLEMENTED.  NOW WE NEED THE USE OF LCORE$ TO    @G@@@@DECREAEH

)@@G@@ITS SPACE.  THIS WILL REQUIRE THE DEFINITION OF A NEW MACRO TO GIVE     EJ
)@@G@@@G@@@@SPACE BACK TO THE SYSTEM, AND THE ADDITION OF CODE AT THE END OF TEK
)@@G@@HE    @F@@@@GARBAGE COLLECTOR THAT CHECKS WHETHER THE AMOUNT OF SPACE REEL
)@@G@@TURNED@G@@@@MINUS THE AMOUNT NEEDED IS GREATER THAN SOME AMOUNT (SAY, 10EM
)@@G@@000 DESC-   @A@@@@RIPTORS) AND RETURN SOME IF IT IS.  @G@@@@************EN
)@@G@@************************************************************@^@@@@PROGRAEO
)@@G@@M TERMINATION.    @G@@@@   CURRENTLY THERE ARE STILL A LOT OF WAYS THAT EP
)@@G@@EXEC8 CAN INTERRUPT     @G@@@@A SNOBOL4 PROGRAM, AND THE TERMINAL MESSAGEQ
)@@G@@ES PRINTED ARE GENERALLY OF   @F@@@@NO VALUE TO THE PROGRAMMER, BECAUSE ER
)@@G@@THEY REFER TO AN ACTION OF THE@F@@@@SNOBOL4 INTERPRETER, NOT TO AN ACTIOES
)@@G@@N OF HIS PROGRAM.  THIS SHOULD@G@@@@BE CHANGED TO MAKE THE EXEC GIVE CONET

)@@G@@ SO THAT A SNOBOL4 TERMINATION CAN BE     @F@@@@DONE TELLING THE PROGRAMEV
)@@G@@MER WHERE HIS PROGRAM WAS AND WHAT IT WAS @G@@@@DOING WHEN INTERRUPTED. EW
)@@G@@ THIS HAS BEEN DONE ALREADY FOR TIME LIMITS;    @A@@@@IT SHOULD BE DONE EX
)@@G@@FOR EVERYTHING.   @G@@@@************************************************EY
)@@G@@************************@#@@@@EXTERNAL FUNCTIONS@G@@@@   THERE IS A MECHEZ
)@@G@@ANISM WITHIN SNOBOL4 FOR THE RUN-TIME LINKING AND     @G@@@@EXECUTION OFFA
)@@G@@ 'EXTERNAL' FUNCTIONS.  THIS HASN'T BEEN INTERFACED WITH    @G@@@@EXEC8 FB
)@@G@@YET, AND OBVIOUSLY SHOULD BE.  THIS WILL MEAN FINDING A WAY TO    @F@@@@FC

)@@G@@PROGRAM.  IT CURRENTLY ISN'T KNOWN WHETHER THIS IS EVEN POSSIBLE. @G@@@@FE
)@@G@@************************************************************************FF
)@@G@@@#@@@@I/O EXTENSIONS.   @G@@@@   SINCE THE 1108 USES SYMBOLIC NAMES FOR FG
)@@G@@FILES, RATHER THAN NUMBERS,   @G@@@@SNOBOL4 SHOULD BE EXTENDED TO ALLOW FH
)@@G@@THE USE OF EITHER.  TO BE SPECIFIC, @G@@@@THE FUNCTIONS INPUT() AND OUTPFI
)@@G@@UT() SHOULD BE MADE TO ACCEPT STRINGS     @F@@@@WHERE THEY NOW ONLY ACCEFJ
)@@G@@PT INTEGERS AS FILE NAMES.  THE CONCEPT OF@G@@@@'LOGICAL UNIT NUMBERS' MFK

)@@G@@ SNOBOL4 SYSTEMS. @F@@@@  ALSO, I/O WITH ELEMENTS OF PROGRAM FILES (AT LFM
)@@G@@EAST WITH SYMBOLIC@F@@@@ELEMENTS) NEEDS TO BE ADDED.  AND SOMETHING LIKEFN
)@@G@@ THE IOTP ROUTINES@F@@@@SHOULD BE ADDED, SO THAT A SNOBOL4 PROGRAM CAN DFO
)@@G@@O I/O WITH NON-SDF@F@@@@FILES.  THIS IS A RATHER IMPORTANT CAPABILITY FOFP
)@@G@@R A LANGUAGE, ONE @D@@@@OF WHOSE MAJOR FEATURES IS ITS MACHINE INDEPENDEFQ
)@@G@@NCE.  @G@@@@************************************************************FR
)@@G@@************@ @@@@FORTRAN-TO-SNOBOL4 TRANSLATOR @G@@@@   AS A PARTIAL SOFS

)@@G@@INTERESTING TO TRY SPECIFYING A SUBSET OF SNOBOL4 THAT CAN BE TRANSLATEDGA

)@@G@@******************************************@#@@@@SNOBOL4 LIBRARY.  @G@@@@GW
)@@G@@   A SNOBOL4 LIBRARY NOW EXISTS.  IT IS RATHER EMPTY, THOUGH, AND AN    GX

)@@G@@TTEN, AND GET AHOLD OF THE    @F@@@@BEST ROUTINES AVAILABLE.  THIS MEANSHD

)@@G@@ THEM.@G@@@@************************************************************HJ
)@@G@@************@#@@@@CONTROL CARDS.    @G@@@@   THERE SHOULD BE A NEW FUNCTHK
)@@G@@ION DEFINED WHICH PASSES CONTROL CARDS    @G@@@@TO THE EXECUTIVE SYSTEM.HL
)@@G@@  THIS WOULD, OF COURSE, BE HIGHLY MACHINE-     @G@@@@DEPENDENT, BUT THEHM

)@@G@@CH THING, AND THERE ARE PROBABLY A LOT OF OTHER OPERATING   @ @@@@SYSTEMHO
)@@G@@S WITH SIMILAR PROBLEMS.@G@@@@******************************************HP
)@@G@@******************************@#@@@@TYPE RESTRICTIONS.@G@@@@   THERE IS HQ
)@@G@@CURRENTLY A MECHANISM WITHIN SNOBOL4 THAT GUARANTEES THAT   @G@@@@A VALUHR
)@@G@@E ASSIGNED TO A KEYWORD IS AN INTEGER, AND DOES A CONVERSION IF   @F@@@@HS
)@@G@@IT ISN'T.  THIS COULD VERY PROFITABLY BE GENERALIZED TO PROVIDE A @G@@@@HT
)@@G@@SIMILAR FACILITY TO THE PROGRAMMER FOR HIS OWN NAMES.  THIS COULD BE    HU
)@@G@@@D@@@@DONE AS FOLLOWS:  SET UP TWO NEW SYSTEM FUNCTIONS:    @ @@@@      HV
)@@G@@RESTRICT(NAME,TYPE)     @^@@@@      UNRESTRICT(NAME)  @G@@@@THE FIRST WOHW
)@@G@@ULD MARK $NAME SO THAT ANYTHING ASSIGNED TO IT IS CONVERTED @G@@@@TO THEHX
)@@G@@ SPECIFIED TYPE, WITH FAILURE OF THE ASSIGNMENT (OR AN 'ILLEGAL   @G@@@@HY
)@@G@@TYPE' ERROR) IF THE CONVERSION FAILS.  THE VALUE IT HAS WHEN RESTRICT() HZ
)@@G@@@G@@@@IS CALLED WOULD ALSO HAVE TO BE CHECKED AND CONVERTED IF NECESSARYIA
)@@G@@,     @G@@@@WITH FAILURE OF RESTRICT() IF THE CONVERSION FAILS.  UNRESTRIB
)@@G@@ICT(NAME)   @G@@@@WOULD RETURN $NAME TO ITS NORMAL STATUS OF BEING ABLE IC
)@@G@@TO ACCEPT A VALUE @]@@@@OF ANY TYPE.@G@@@@   THESE TWO FUNCTIONS CAN, OFID
)@@G@@ COURSE, BE DEFINED NOW BY THE PROGRAMMER @G@@@@AS TRACING FUNCTIONS.  BIE
)@@G@@UT THERE IS A GOOD REASON FOR MAKING THEM A     @G@@@@PART OF THE LANGUAIF
)@@G@@GE ITSELF.  THIS IS THE USE OF SUCH A TYPE-RESTRICTING@G@@@@CAPABILITY TIG
)@@G@@O IMPROVE THE 'EFFICIENCY' OF PROGRAMS.  CURRENTLY, IT IS   @F@@@@COMMONIH
)@@G@@ TO FOLLOW MANY PATTERN MATCHES (ESPECIALLY THOSE ANALYZING @G@@@@INPUT)II
)@@G@@ WITH A SERIES OF TYPE CONVERSIONS, USUALLY TO CONVERT NUMERIC    @F@@@@IJ
)@@G@@STRINGS TO NUMBERS, SO THAT THE CODE USING THEM WON'T HAVE TO DO A@G@@@@IK
)@@G@@LOT OF CONVERTING.  THIS HAS TWO 'INEFFICIENCIES' THAT RESTRICT() WOULD IL
)@@G@@@G@@@@ELIMINATE IF HANDLED DIRECTLY BY SNOBOL4.  THE VALUE IS FIRST ASSIIM
)@@G@@GNED  @G@@@@AS ONE TYPE, THEN THIS VALUE IS CONVERTED AND ASSIGNED AS ANIN
)@@G@@OTHER TYPE. @G@@@@THIS REQUIRES TWO ASSIGNMENTS WHERE ONE WOULD SUFFICE.IO
)@@G@@  AND A SEPARATE  @G@@@@STATEMENT IS NEEDED FOR THE CONVERSION, WHICH TAIP
)@@G@@KES UP SPACE (AND THERE @F@@@@IS ALSO OVERHEAD ASSOCIATED WITH STARTING IQ
)@@G@@EACH STATEMENT, SUCH AS @B@@@@UPDATING &STCOUNT, &STNO, AND &LASTNO).   IR
)@@G@@@G@@@@   THERE IS ALSO THE FACT THAT SUCH INFORMATION COULD BE VERY VALUIS
)@@G@@ABLE  @G@@@@TO A MACHINE-CODE GENERATING COMPILER, SUCH AS HAS BEEN WRITIT
)@@G@@TEN FOR THE @G@@@@360.  MUCH FASTER CODE COULD BE PRODUCED IF THE COMPILIU
)@@G@@ER COULD DETER-   @G@@@@MINE THAT A VARIABLE'S VALUE IS ALWAYS GOING TO IV
)@@G@@BE OF ONE PARTICULAR    @G@@@@TYPE.  THIS WOULD IN FACT CORRESPOND TO THIW
)@@G@@E TYPE DECLARATIONS (EXPLICIT @C@@@@OR NOT) USED IN LANGUAGES LIKE FORTRIX
)@@G@@AN OR ALGOL.@G@@@@******************************************************IY
)@@G@@******************@F@@@@ARITHMETIC EXTENSIONS--DOUBLE PRECISION AND COMPIZ
)@@G@@LEX ARITHMETIC.   @G@@@@   MOST LARGE COMPUTERS HAVE DOUBLE-PRECISION HAJA
)@@G@@RDWARE, AT LEAST FOR    @F@@@@FLOATING-POINT IF NOT FOR INTEGERS.  IT WOJB

)@@G@@************************************************************************JM
)@@G@@@ @@@@MULTI-PROGRAMMING CAPABILITY. @F@@@@   THE SNOBOL4 EXEC SHOULD BE JN
)@@G@@MADE INTO A MULTI-PROGRAMMING EXEC. @G@@@@THE MOST OBVIOUS JUSTIFICATIONJO
)@@G@@ FOR THIS IS THE FACT THAT THE SNOBOL4    @F@@@@EXEC USES ABOUT 35,000 WJP
)@@G@@ORDS ON THE 1108, AND CURRENTLY THERE IS A@G@@@@SEPARATE COPY FOR EACH SJQ
)@@G@@NOBOL PROGRAM.  IF THERE WERE A MULTI-PROGRAMMED@G@@@@VERSION OF SNOBOL,JR
)@@G@@ ONLY ONE COPY OF IT WOULD BE NEEDED, NO MATTER HOW   @G@@@@MANY PROGRAMJS
)@@G@@S WERE BEING RUN.  OF COURSE, IT WOULD PROBABLY USE MORE    @G@@@@LIKE 4JT
)@@G@@0,000 WORDS, BUT THIS DOESN'T AFFECT THE ARGUMENT MUCH.  THIS     @G@@@@JU
)@@G@@WOULD BE ESPECIALLY INTERESTING WHEN THE MACHINE-INDEPENDENT NATURE OF  JV
)@@G@@@F@@@@SNOBOL4 IS CONSIDERED--THE RESULT WOULD BE A MACHINE-INDEPENDENT  JW
)@@G@@@G@@@@OPERATING SYSTEM.  SUCH A THING WOULD BE VALUABLE FOR THE PUBLICITJX
)@@G@@Y     @B@@@@IT WOULD RECEIVE, IF FOR NO OTHER REASON. @G@@@@************JY
)@@G@@************************************************************@^@@@@INFORMJZ
)@@G@@ATIVE DIAGNOSTICS.@F@@@@   A SET OF 'INFORMATIVE' OR 'WARNING' MESSAGES KA
)@@G@@WOULD BE A USEFUL @F@@@@DEBUGGING TOOL.  THE SIMPLEST WAY TO DO THIS WOUKB
)@@G@@LD BE AS FOLLOWS. @G@@@@A NEW KEYWORD, &INFORM, IS DEFINED THAT CONTROLSKC
)@@G@@ THE PRINTING OF SUCH   @G@@@@MESSAGES.  IF &INFORM > 0, THE OCCURRENCE KD
)@@G@@OF ANY OF A SET OF CONDITIONS @G@@@@WILL CAUSE A MESSAGE TO BE PRINTED, KE
)@@G@@DESCRIBING THE CONDITION AND WHERE  @G@@@@IT OCCURRED.  IF &INFORM = 0, KF
)@@G@@THE MESSAGE WILL BE SUPPRESSED.  SOME SUCH@#@@@@CONDITIONS ARE:   @D@@@@KG
)@@G@@   1) CONDITIONALLY FATAL ERRORS, WITH &ERRLIMIT > 0. @A@@@@   2) RE-DEFKH
)@@G@@INITION OF FUNCTIONS.   @F@@@@   3) DEFINITION OF A FUNCTION WITH AN UNDKI
)@@G@@EFINED ENTRY POINT.     @F@@@@   4) COMPILING CODE THAT CONTAINS REFERENKJ

)@@G@@@G@@@@       AA,U   A0,2                 A(OCBSCL) +                    MN
)@@G@@ JC01 @G@@@@       SA     A0,OCICL.               (A(OCICL) := A(OCICL) MO
)@@G@@+ 2);  JC01 @G@@@@       AA     A0,OCBSCL.                              MP
)@@G@@             JC01 @G@@@@       DL     A0,0,A0.                          MQ
)@@G@@                   JC01 @G@@@@       DS     A0,XPTR.             PUT INTMR
)@@G@@O XPTR.                  JC01 @G@@@@       SSC    A1,18.               TMS
)@@G@@EST FOR FUNCTION:              JC01 @G@@@@       TOP,U  A1,FNC.         MT
)@@G@@     IF FNC FLAG NOT SET             JC01 @G@@@@       J      INTERP.   MU
)@@G@@              THEN IGNORE THIS DESCR.      JC01 @]@@@@-1600,1607  @G@@@@MV
)@@G@@       LON.                                                        JC01 MW
)@@G@@@G@@@@INVOKE.                            FUNCTION INVOCATION PROCEDURE  MX
)@@G@@ JC01 @G@@@@       LXI,XU CSTACK,-2.           POP ARG FROM STACK;      MY
)@@G@@       JC01 @G@@@@       DL     A0,0,*CSTACK.                           MZ
)@@G@@             JC01 @G@@@@INVOKA0.                           (ALTERNATE ENNA
)@@G@@TRY--ARG IN A0/1)  JC01 @G@@@@       DS     A0,INCL.             INCL :=NB
)@@G@@ ARG;                    JC01 @G@@@@       LA,H2  A2,1,A0.             ANC
)@@G@@2 := V-FIELD OF FCT ENTRY      JC01 @G@@@@       TNE,H2 A2,INCL+1.      ND
)@@G@@     IF V-FIELDS (# OF PARAMS) AGREE JC01 @G@@@@INVK1  J      *0,A0.    NE
)@@G@@              THEN CALL A(INCL).           JC01 @G@@@@       LA,H1  A2,1NF
)@@G@@,A0.             IF DIFFERENT,                   JC01 @G@@@@       TEP,UNG

)@@G@@       JC16 @G@@@[. JC17 CORRECTS THE HANDLING OF L-FIELDS OF SPECIFIERSTZ

)@@G@@ JC17 @G@@@[. OF A BUG).  AND SINCE A HALF-WORD OPERATION ON THE 1108 COUL

)@@G@@***********************************ACOMP***JC03             @I@@@@. ACOMWG
)@@G@@P  D1,D2,GT,EQ,LT.           'ADDRESS COMPARE'               JC03       WH
)@@G@@      @I@@@@.                                                           WI
)@@G@@       JC03             @I@@@@. IF A(D1) > A(D2) THEN GO TO GT;         WJ
)@@G@@                         JC03             @I@@@@. IF A(D1) = A(D2) THEN WK
)@@G@@GO TO EQ;                                  JC03             @I@@@@. IF AWL
)@@G@@(D1) < A(D2) THEN GO TO LT;                                  JC03       WM
)@@G@@      @I@@@@.                                                           WN
)@@G@@       JC03             @I@@@@. THE A-FIELDS AREN'T USED AS ADDRESSES, SWO
)@@G@@O THERE IS NO ADDRESS    JC03             @I@@@@. LIMITATION TO 64K. TO WP
)@@G@@UNDERSTAND THIS PROC'S EXPANSION, IT IS    JC03             @I@@@@. NECEWQ
)@@G@@SSARY TO REALIZE THAT THE JP AND JN COMMANDS CAN BOTH CAUSE  JC03       WR
)@@G@@      @I@@@@. A JUMP ON 0--THEY ONLY TEST THE SIGN BIT.  SO IF A(D1)-A(DWS
)@@G@@2) = 0,JC03             @I@@@@. IT IS NECESSARY TO DO A JUMP--TO THE EQ WT
)@@G@@EXIT IF IT EXISTS, AND   JC03             @I@@@@. AROUND THE OTHER TESTSWU
)@@G@@ IF IT DOESN'T                             JC03             @I@@@@.     WV
)@@G@@                                                             JC03       WW
)@@G@@      @G@@@[. NOTE THAT A SUBTRACTION IS DONE, FOLLOWED BY TESTS FOR ZERWX
)@@G@@O,     JC00 @G@@@[. NEGATIVE, AND POSITIVE.  IF ABS(A(D1) - A(D2)) >= 2*WY
)@@G@@*35, THIS    JC00 @G@@@[. WILL RESULT IN AN OVERFLOW AND A TRANSFER TO AWZ
)@@G@@ERROR.  THIS MEANS JC00 @G@@@[. THAT SOME PAIRS OF INTEGERS CAN'T BE COMXA
)@@G@@PARED.  THIS PROBLEM     JC00 @G@@@[. IS SHARED BY ALL THE OTHER COMPARIXB
)@@G@@SON MACROS.  THE REASON A      JC00 @G@@@[. DIRECT COMPARISON ISN'T MADEXC
)@@G@@ IS THAT THE 1108 LACKS A NUMERIC    JC00 @G@@@[. EQUALITY (OR INEQUALITXD
)@@G@@Y) TEST.  THE SO-CALLED 'EQUALITY' TESTS   JC00 @G@@@[. ARE REALLY IDENTXE
)@@G@@ITY TESTS, AND THEY CONSIDER TWO DIFFERENT       JC00 @G@@@[. REPRESENTAXF
)@@G@@TIONS OF THE SAME NUMBER TO BE UNEQUAL.  FOR INTEGERS, JC00 @G@@@[. THISXG
)@@G@@ MEANS THAT 0 AND -0 ARE UNEQUAL.  FOR REALS, THE PROBLEM    JC00 @G@@@[XH
)@@G@@. IS MORE GENERAL.  IT MIGHT BE POSSIBLE TO TEST INTEGERS WITH THE JC00 XI
)@@G@@@G@@@[. 'TG' AND 'TLE' INSTRUCTIONS, BUT THIS TAKES OVER TWICE AS MANY  XJ
)@@G@@ JC00 @G@@@[. INSTRUCTIONS AS THE DEFINITIONS INVOLVING SUBTRACTION.    XK
)@@G@@       JC00 @G@@@[.                                                     XL
)@@G@@             JC00 @I@@@@. A0 IS USED.                                   XM
)@@G@@                   JC03             @I@@@@.                             XN
)@@G@@                                     JC03             @I@@@@ACOMP**   PRXO
)@@G@@OC      1.                                             JC03             XP
)@@G@@@I@@@@GTE       EQU      1-ACOMP(1,*3).       GT EXISTS.                XQ
)@@G@@ JC03             @I@@@@EQE       EQU      1-ACOMP(1,*4).       EQ EXISTXR
)@@G@@S.                 JC03             @I@@@@LTE       EQU      1-ACOMP(1,*XS
)@@G@@5).       LT EXISTS.                 JC03             @I@@@@.           XT
)@@G@@                                                       JC03             XU
)@@G@@@I@@@@          LA        A0,ACOMP(1,1).      A(D1)                     XV
)@@G@@ JC03             @I@@@@          ANA       A0,ACOMP(1,2).      - A(D2) XW
)@@G@@                   JC03             @G@@@[          JO        AERROR.   XX
)@@G@@          CHECK FOR OVERFLOW         JC12 @I@@@@          JZ        A0,EXY
)@@G@@Q.              EQ TEST--ALWAYS NEEDED.    JC03             @I@@@@ DO GTXZ
)@@G@@E , JP        A0,ACOMP(1,3).      GT TEST.                   JC03       YA
)@@G@@      @I@@@@ DO LTE , JN        A0,ACOMP(1,5).      LT TEST.            YB
)@@G@@       JC03             @I@@@@EQ        LOCC      ACOMP(1,4),$.       EQYC
)@@G@@ EXIT HERE IF OMITTED.   JC03             @I@]@@          LOFF.         YD
)@@G@@                                           JC00             @I[@@@      YE
)@@G@@    END.                                                     JC03       YF
)@@G@@      @I@@@@. *********************************************************AYG
)@@G@@COMP***JC03             @I@@@@. ****************************************YH
)@@G@@*****************ACOMPC**JC00             @I@@@@.  ACOMPC  DE,N,GT,EQ,LTYI
)@@G@@.          'ADDRESS COMPARE WITH CONSTANT' JC05             @I@@@@.     YJ
)@@G@@                                                             JC05       YK
)@@G@@      @I@@@@.  IF A(DE) > N THEN GO TO GT;                              YL
)@@G@@       JC05             @I@@@@.  IF A(DE) = N THEN GO TO EQ;            YM
)@@G@@                         JC05             @I@@@@.  IF A(DE) < N THEN GO YN
)@@G@@TO LT;                                     JC05             @I@@@@.     YO
)@@G@@                                                             JC05       YP
)@@G@@      @I@[@@.  N MUST BE < 65536.                                       YQ
)@@G@@       JC05             @G@@@[.  N IS LIMITED TO 17 BITS AND A SIGN.    YR
)@@G@@                         JC05 @I@@@@.  SEE THE COMMENTS FOR ACOMP.      YS
)@@G@@                               JC05             @I@@@@.  A0 USED.       YT
)@@G@@                                                 JC05             @I@@@@YU
)@@G@@.                                                                  JC05 YV
)@@G@@            @I@@@@ACOMPC**  PROC      1.                                YW
)@@G@@             JC05             @I@@@@NNZ       EQU       1-ACOMPC(1,*2). YX
)@@G@@    N IS NON-ZERO.             JC05             @I@@@@GTE       EQU     YY
)@@G@@  1-ACOMPC(1,*3).     GT EXISTS.                 JC05             @I@@@@YZ
)@@G@@LTE       EQU       1-ACOMPC(1,*5).     LT EXISTS.                 JC05 ZA
)@@G@@            @I@@@@.                                                     ZB
)@@G@@             JC05             @I@@@@          LA        A0,ACOMPC(1,1). ZC
)@@G@@    A(DE)                      JC05             @I@[@@ DO NNZ , ANA,U   ZD
)@@G@@  A0,ACOMPC(1,2).     -N, IF NECESSARY.          JC05             @G@@@[ZE
)@@G@@ DO NNZ , ANA,XU    A0,ACOMPC(1,2).     -N, IF NECESSARY.          JC05 ZF
)@@G@@@G@@@[ DO NNZ , JO        AERROR.             TEST FOR OVERFLOW.        ZG
)@@G@@ JC12 @I@@@@          JZ        A0,EQ.              EQ TEST--ALWAYS NEEDZH
)@@G@@ED.    JC05             @I@@@@ DO GTE , JP        A0,ACOMPC(1,3).     GTZI
)@@G@@ TEST.                   JC05             @I@@@@ DO LTE , JN        A0,AZJ
)@@G@@COMPC(1,5).     LT TEST.                   JC05             @I@@@@.     ZK
)@@G@@                                                             JC05       ZL
)@@G@@      @I@@@@EQ        LOCC      ACOMPC(1,4),$.      EQ HERE IF OMITTED. ZM
)@@G@@       JC05             @I@]@@          LOFF.                           ZN
)@@G@@                         JC05             @I[@@@          END.          ZO

)@@G@@DDFST**JC15             @I@@@@. ADDFST  DE,FAIL,SUCC.            'ADD TOZS
)@@G@@ FREE STORAGE AREA'      JC15             @I@@@@.                       ZT
)@@G@@                                           JC15             @I@@@@. THISZU
)@@G@@ INCREASES THE AMOUNT OF FREE STORAGE BY AT LEAST A(DE)      JC15       ZV
)@@G@@      @I@@@@. WORDS.  IF THIS ISN'T POSSIBLE, TRANSFER IS TO FAIL; OTHERZW
)@@G@@WISE   JC15             @I@@@@. TRANSFER IS TO SUCC.  THE GLOBAL DESCRIPZX
)@@G@@TOR, TLSGP1, IS SET TO   JC15             @I@@@@. ONE GREATER THAN THE LZY
)@@G@@AST ACCESSIBLE ADDRESS.  MORE THAN A(DE)   JC15             @I@@@@. CAN ZZ
)@@G@@BE PROVIDED--E.G., IF SPACE MUST BE ALLOCATED IN MULTI-WORD  JC15       AA
)@@G@@      @I@@@@. CHUNKS, SUCH AS PAGES--AND TLSGP1 SHOULD REFLECT THE ACTUAAB
)@@G@@L      JC15             @I@@@@. SPACE ALLOCATED SO THAT IT CAN ALL BE USAC
)@@G@@ED.                      JC15             @I@@@@.                       AD
)@@G@@                                           JC15             @I@@@@ADDFSTAE
)@@G@@**  PROC      1.                                             JC15       AF
)@@G@@      @I@@@@SE        EQU       1-ADDFST(1,*3).     SUCCESS EXIT EXISTS.AG
)@@G@@       JC15             @I@@@@.                                         AH
)@@G@@                         JC15             @I@@@@          LA        A0,AAI
)@@G@@DDFST(1,1).     A(DE) = SIZE IN WORDS.     JC15             @I@@@@      AJ
)@@G@@    AA        A0,TLSGP1.     ADD CURRENT END OF FREE STORAGE JC15       AK
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          TG        A0,FSTMAX.     ABOVE LIMIT?             AL
)@@G@@       JC15             @I@@@@          J         FAIL.          YES--FAAM
)@@G@@IL.                      JC15             @I@@@@          ER        MCORAN
)@@G@@E$.        NO--GET THE SPACE.              JC15             @I@@@@      AO
)@@G@@    AND,U     A0,0777.       A1 = LAST 3 BITS OF ADDRESS     JC15       AP
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          ANA       A0,A1.         SET TAIL TO 0.           AQ
)@@G@@       JC15             @I@@@@          AA,U      A0,01000.      ADD 512AR
)@@G@@--SIZE OF MEMORY CHUNK   JC15             @I@@@@          SA        A0,TAS
)@@G@@LSGP1.     PUT IT INTO TLSGP1.             JC15             @I@@@@ DO SEAT
)@@G@@ ,  J         ADDFST(1,3).   JUMP IF SUCCESS EXIT            JC15       AU
)@@G@@      @I@@@@.                                                           AV
)@@G@@       JC15             @I@@@@FAIL      LOCC      ADDFST(1,2),$. FAIL EXAW
)@@G@@IT HERE IF OMITTED.      JC15             @I@@@@          END.      ADDFAX
)@@G@@ST.                                        JC15             @I@@@@. ****AY
)@@G@@*****************************************************ADDFST**JC15       AZ
)@@G@@      @I@@@@. *********************************************************CBA
)@@G@@OMP****JC03             @I@@@@COMP***   PROC      1.                    BB
)@@G@@                                          @I@@@@GT        EQU       COMPBC
)@@G@@(1,*3).                                                     @I@@@@EQ    BD
)@@G@@    EQU       COMP(1,*4).                                               BE
)@@G@@      @I@@@@LT        EQU       COMP(1,*5).                             BF

)@@G@@                                          @I@@@@          ANA       A0,CBH
)@@G@@OMP(1,2-LT).                                                @I@@@@      BI

)@@G@@                        @I@@@@  DO 1-(LT++GT) , J COMP(1,3).            BL
)@@G@@                                          @I@@@@EQEXIT    LOCC      COMPBM
)@@G@@(1,4),$.                                   JC02             @I@@@@      BN
)@@G@@    END.      COMP.                                          JC05       BO

)@@G@@DDSIB**JC00             @I@@@@. ADDSIB  D1,D2.              'ADD SIBLINGCA
)@@G@@'                        JC00             @I@@@@.                       CB
)@@G@@                                           JC00             @I@@@@. ADDSCC
)@@G@@ THE NODE D2 AS A 'SIBLING' OF THE NODE D1.  THIS IS REALLY JJC00       CD
)@@G@@      @I@@@@. A LIST-INSERT OPERATION.  THE RELEVANT FIELDS OF A NODE N CE
)@@G@@ARE:   JC00             @I@@@@.    N+FATHER = ADDR. OF THE NODE'S IMMEDICF
)@@G@@ATE ANCESTOR             JC00             @I@@@@.    N+RSIB   = FIRST NOCG
)@@G@@DE IN LIST OF SIBLINGS.                    JC00             @I@@@@.    NCH
)@@G@@+LSON   = FIRST SON--SONS ARE LINKED THRU RSIB FIELD.        JC00       CI
)@@G@@      @I@@@@.    N+CODE   = NUMBER OF SONS IN LSON LIST.                CJ
)@@G@@       JC00             @I@@@@. A STANDARD LIST-INSERT OPERATION IS DONECK
)@@G@@.  IT MIGHT BE A GOOD IDEJC00             @I@@@@. TO REWRITE THIS AS A SCL
)@@G@@UBROUTINE CALL SOMEDAY, SINCE IT IS CALLED JC00             @I@@@@. A LOCM
)@@G@@T AND USES A FAIR AMOUNT OF SPACE.                           JC00       CN
)@@G@@      @I@@@@. THIS SHOULD WORK FOR > 64K.                               CO
)@@G@@       JC00             @I@@@@.                                         CP
)@@G@@                         JC00             @I@@@@ADDSIB**  PROC      1,10CQ
)@@G@@.               ADD SIBLING TO TREE NODE                    @I@@@@      CR
)@@G@@    LA        A0,ADDSIB(1,1).                                           CS
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          DL        A1,ADDSIB(1,2).                         CT
)@@G@@                        @I@@@@          DL        A3,FATHER,A0.         CU
)@@G@@                                          @I@@@@         LA,H2  A10,CODECV
)@@G@@+1,A3.                                                      @I@@@@      CW
)@@G@@   AA,U   A10,1.                                                        CX
)@@G@@      @I@@@@         SA,H2  A10,CODE+1,A3.                              CY
)@@G@@                        @I@@@@          DL        A5,RSIB,A0.           CZ
)@@G@@                                          @I@@@@          DS        A3,FDA
)@@G@@ATHER,A1.                                                   @I@@@@      DB
)@@G@@    DS        A5,RSIB,A1.                                               DC
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          DS        A1,RSIB,A0.                             DD
)@@G@@                        @I@@@@          END.                            DE
)@@G@@                                          @I@@@@. **********************DF
)@@G@@***********************************ADDSIB**JC00             @I@@@@. ****DG

)@@G@@@I@[@@EQL**     PROC      1.                                            FH
)@@G@@                  @I@[@@AEQL**    NAME      0.                 ADDRESSESFI
)@@G@@ EQUAL TEST                         @I@[@@VEQL**    NAME      011.      FJ
)@@G@@         VALUE FIELDS EQUAL TEST                      @I@[@@NM        EQFK
)@@G@@U       EQL(0,0).                                                       FL
)@@G@@@I@[@@UF1       EQUF      EQL(1,1)+(NM**7),,NM/8.                       FM
)@@G@@                  @I@[@@UF2       EQUF      EQL(1,2)+(NM**7),,NM/8.     FN
)@@G@@                                    @I@[@@NE        EQU       EQL(1,*3).FO
)@@G@@                                                      @I@[@@EQ        EQFP
)@@G@@U       EQL(1,*4).                                                      FQ
)@@G@@@I@[@@          LA        A0,UF1.                                       FR
)@@G@@                  @I@[@@  DO NE , TNE       A0,UF2.                     FS
)@@G@@                                    @I@[@@  DO 1-NE , TE      A0,UF2.   FT
)@@G@@                                                      @I@[@@          J FU
)@@G@@        EQL(1,3+NE).                                                    FV

)@@G@@                  @I@[@@          LOFF.                                 FX
)@@G@@                   JC10             @I@[@@          END.                FY

)@@G@@*JC13*@G@@@[. AEQL  D1,D2,NE,EQ.               'ADDRESS EQUALITY TEST'  GC
)@@G@@       JC13 @G@@@[.                                                     GD

)@@G@@E GO TO NE.                    JC13 @G@@@[. EITHER EXIT MAY BE OMITTED, GH
)@@G@@BUT NOT BOTH.                        JC13 @G@@@[.                       GI

)@@G@@***********************************AEQLIC**JC00             @I@@@@. AEQLIE

)@@G@@      @I@@@@.                                                           IG

)@@G@@ < 65536.                                  JC03             @G@@@[. N1 MIJ

)@@G@@             JC03             @I@@@@AEQLIC**  PROC      1.              IN

)@@G@@            @I@[@@   DO NEE ,   TZ    A0.                 PRODUCE APPROPIW

)@@G@@   DO EQE ,   J     AEQLIC(1,5).        EQ EXIT.                   JC03 JA
)@@G@@            @G@@@[ DO N2E , ANA,XU    A0,AEQLIC(1,2).     - N2, IF NONZEJB
)@@G@@RO.          JC03 @G@@@[ DO NEE , JNZ       A0,AEQLIC(1,4).     NE EXIT.JC
)@@G@@                   JC03 @G@@@[ DO EQE , JZ        A0,AEQLIC(1,5).     EQJD
)@@G@@ EXIT.                   JC03 @I@@@@          END.                      JE
)@@G@@                               JC03             @I@@@@. ****************JF
)@@G@@*****************************************AEQLIC**JC03             @I@@@@JG
)@@G@@. *********************************************************APDSP***JC00 JH
)@@G@@            @I@@@@. APDSP  S1,S2.               'APPEND SPECIFIER'      JI
)@@G@@             JC04             @I@@@@.                                   JJ
)@@G@@                               JC04             @I@@@@. THIS IS THE INSTJK
)@@G@@RUCTION USED FOR COPYING STRINGS.  THE STRING    JC04             @I@]@@JL
)@@G@@. POINTED TO BY THE SPECIFIER S1 IS COPIED INTO THE SPACE IMMEDIATEJC04 JM
)@@G@@            @I@]@@. AFTER THE STRING POINTED TO BY S1.  TO BE EXACT, THEJN
)@@G@@ STRING OF L(JC04             @I@]@@. CHARACTERS STARTING AT A(S2)+O(S2)JO
)@@G@@ IS TO BE COPIED TO THE LOCATIOJC04             @I@]@@. A(S1)+O(S1)+L(S1JP
)@@G@@). (NOTE THAT THE A-FIELD IS IN UNITS OF WORDS,  JC04             @I@]@@JQ
)@@G@@. WHILE THE O- AND L-FIELDS ARE IN UNITS OF CHARACTERS.)  THE L-FIEJC04 JR
)@@G@@            @I@]@@. OF S1 IS TO BE INCREASED TO L(S1)+L(S2), MAKING THE JS
)@@G@@COPIED STRINGJC04             @I@]@@. PART OF S1.  IT IS UP TO THE CODE JT
)@@G@@PRECEDING THE CALL OF APDSP TO JC04             @I@]@@. ENSURE THAT THE JU
)@@G@@COPY WILL NOT OVERWRITE ANYTHING OF VALUE, SINCE JC04             @I@]@@JV
)@@G@@. APDSP DOESN'T (AND IN FACT CAN'T) CHECK THIS.                    JC04 JW
)@@G@@            @I@]@@.                                                     JX
)@@G@@             JC04             @I@]@@. X1-X3, A0-A5 ARE USED.            JY
)@@G@@                               JC04             @G@@[]. POINTED TO BY THJZ
)@@G@@E SPECIFIER S2 IS COPIED INTO THE SPACE JUST     JC04 @G@@[]. AFTER THE KA
)@@G@@STRING POINTED TO BY S1.  TO BE EXACT, THE STRONG OF   JC04 @G@@[]. L(S2KB
)@@G@@) CHARACTERS STARTING AT A(S2) + O(S2) IS COPIED TO THE      JC04 @G@@[]KC
)@@G@@. LOCATION A(S1) + O(S1) + L(S1).  (NOTE THAT THE A-FIELD IS IN    JC04 KD
)@@G@@@G@@[]. UNITS OF WORDS, WHILE THE O- AND L-FIELDS ARE IN UNITS OF CHAR- KE
)@@G@@ JC04 @G@@[]. ACTERS.)  THE L-FIELD OF S1 IS INCREASED TO L(S1) + L(S2),KF
)@@G@@       JC04 @G@@[]. MAKING THE COPIED STRING PART OF S1.  IT IS UP TO THKG
)@@G@@E CODE       JC04 @G@@[]. PRECEDING THE CALL OF APDSP TO ENSURE THAT THIKH
)@@G@@S WILL NOT OVER-   JC04 @G@@[]. WRITE ANYTHING OF VALUE, SINCE APDSP DOEKI
)@@G@@SN'T (AND IN FACT CAN'T) JC04 @G@@[]. CHECK THIS.                       KJ
)@@G@@                               JC04 @G@@[].                             KK
)@@G@@                                     JC04 @G@@[]. X1-X3, X11, A0-A5 ARE KL
)@@G@@USED.                                      JC04 @IF@@@.                 KM
)@@G@@                                                 JC04             @I@@@@KN
)@@G@@APDSP**   PROC      1,3.                                           JC04 KO
)@@G@@            @I@@@@          LX,U      X2,APDSP(1,1).      X2 = ADDR OF SKP
)@@G@@1.           JC04             @I@@@@          LX,U      X3,APDSP(1,2).  KQ
)@@G@@    X3 = ADDR OF S2.           JC04             @I@@@@          LMJ     KR
)@@G@@  X11,APDSPS.         DO THE MOVE.               JC04             @I@[@@KS
)@@G@@          LOFF.                                                    JC00 KT
)@@G@@            @I@@@@          END.                                        KU
)@@G@@             JC04             @I@@@@. **********************************KV
)@@G@@***********************APDSP***JC00             @I@@@@. ****************KW
)@@G@@*****************************************ARRAY***JC03             @I@@@@KX
)@@G@@. ARRAY  N.                   'RESERVE N DESCRS OF ZEROES'         JC03 KY
)@@G@@            @I@@@@.                                                     KZ
)@@G@@             JC03             @I@@@@. THIS CREATES A BLOCK OF N DESCRIPTLA
)@@G@@ORS OF ZEROES, STARTING AT THE JC03             @I@@@@. PLACE IT IS USEDLB
)@@G@@.                                                                 @I@@@@LC
)@@G@@.                                                                  JC03 LD
)@@G@@            @I@@@@ARRAY**   PROC      1.                                LE
)@@G@@             JC03             @I@@@@ DO 2 ,   RES       ARRAY(1,1).     LF
)@@G@@                               JC03             @I@@@@          END.    LG
)@@G@@                                                 JC03             @I@@@@LH
)@@G@@. *********************************************************ARRAY***JC03 LI
)@@G@@            @I@@@@. ****************************************************LJ
)@@G@@*****BKSIZE**JC00             @I@@@@. BKSIZE  D1,D2.                   'LK
)@@G@@GET BLOCK SIZE'                JC30             @I@@@@.                 LL
)@@G@@                                                 JC30             @I@@@@LM
)@@G@@. A(D2) IS THE ADDRESS OF A BLOCK OF STORAGE, WHOSE SIZE IS TO BE  JC30 LN
)@@G@@            @I@@@@. CALCULATED AND PUT IN A(D1).  IF F(A(D2)) CONTAINS TLO
)@@G@@HE STTL FLAG,JC30             @I@@@@. THE BLOCK IS A STRING AND ITS SIZELP
)@@G@@ IS:                           JC30             @I@@@@.         D * (4 +LQ
)@@G@@ (V(A(D2) - 1) / CPD) + D                        JC30             @I@@@@LR
)@@G@@. IF THE STTL FLAG ISN'T PRESENT, THE BLOCK ISN'T A STRING, AND ITSJC30 LS
)@@G@@            @I@@@@. SIZE IS:                                            LT
)@@G@@             JC30             @I@@@@.         V(A(D2)) + D              LU
)@@G@@                               JC30             @I@@@@.                 LV
)@@G@@                                                 JC30             @I@@@@LW
)@@G@@. A0-A3 USED.                                                      JC30 LX
)@@G@@            @I@@@@.                                                     LY
)@@G@@             JC30             @I@@@@BKSIZE**  PROC      1.              LZ
)@@G@@                               JC30             @I@@@@          LA      MA
)@@G@@  A0,BKSIZE(1,2).     A(D2)                      JC30             @I@@@@MB
)@@G@@          LA,H1     A1,1,A0.            F(A(D2))                   JC30 MC
)@@G@@            @I@@@@          LA,H2     A2,1,A0.            F(A(D2))      MD
)@@G@@             JC30             @I@@@@          TOP,U     A1,STTL.        ME
)@@G@@    IF NO STTL, THEN           JC30             @I@@@@          J       MF
)@@G@@  FIN.                   JUMP AROUND COMPUTATION JC30             @I@@@@MG
)@@G@@.                                  COMPUTE SIZE OF STRING BLOCK:   JC30 MH
)@@G@@            @I@@@@          ANA,U     A2,1.          V(A(D2)) - 1       MI
)@@G@@             JC30             @I@@@@          DSL       A2,36.         PMJ
)@@G@@REPARE FOR DIVIDE:             JC30             @I@@@@          DI,U    MK
)@@G@@  A2,CPD.        (V(A(D2)) - 1) / CPD            JC30             @I@@@@ML
)@@G@@          AA,U      A2,4.          4 + (V(A(D2)) - 1) / CPD        JC30 MM
)@@G@@            @I@@@@          LSSC      A2,1.          D * (4 + (V(A(D2)) MN
)@@G@@- 1) / CPD)  JC30             @I@@@@FIN       AA,U      A2,DESCR.      SMO
)@@G@@IZE + D = FINAL RESULT         JC30             @I@@@@          LA,U    MP
)@@G@@  A3,0.          FV = 0                          JC30             @I@@@@MQ
)@@G@@          DS        A2,BKSIZE(1,1).     PUT IN D1.                 JC30 MR
)@@G@@            @I@[@@          LOFF.                                       MS
)@@G@@             JC30             @I@@@@          END.      BKSIZE.         MT
)@@G@@                               JC30             @I@@@@. ****************MU
)@@G@@*****************************************BKSIZE**JC00             @I@@@@MV
)@@G@@. *********************************************************IO******JC00 MW
)@@G@@            @I@@@@IO**      PROC      1,3.                              MX
)@@G@@                              @I@@@@BKSPCE**  NAME      NBSP$.          MY
)@@G@@   BACKSPACE RECORD                             @I@@@@ENFILE**  NAME    MZ
)@@G@@  NWEF$.             WRITE END OF FILE                            @I@@@@NA
)@@G@@REWIND**  NAME      NREW$.             REWIND FILE                      NB
)@@G@@            @I@@@@          LMJ       X11,IO(0,0).                      NC
)@@G@@                              @I@@@@          +         0,IO(1,1).      ND
)@@G@@                                                @I@@@@          +       NE
)@@G@@  $-START$,0.                                                     @I@@@@NF
)@@G@@          END.                                                          NG
)@@G@@            @I@@@@. ****************************************************NH

)@@G@@*****************************************BRANIC**JC00             @I@@@@NP
)@@G@@. BRANIC  DE,N.     'BRANCH INDIRECT WITH OFFSET CONSTANT'         JC00 NQ
)@@G@@            @I@@@@.                                                     NR
)@@G@@             JC00             @I@@@@. GO TO A(A(DE)+N).                 NS
)@@G@@                               JC00             @I@@@@. BOTH N AND THE FNT
)@@G@@INAL ADDRESS MUST BE < 65536.  AS LONG AS THE    JC00             @I@@@@NU
)@@G@@. I-BANK OF SNOBOL IS LESS THAN THIS SIZE, THIS PROC WILL WORK OK. JC00 NV
)@@G@@            @I@@@@. A(DE) CAN BE > 64K.                                 NW
)@@G@@             JC00             @I@@@@. A0 IS USED.                       NX
)@@G@@                               JC00             @I@@@@.                 NY
)@@G@@                                                                  @I@@@@NZ
)@@G@@BRANIC**  PROC      1,2.              BRANCH INDIRECT WITH OFFSET CONSTAOA
)@@G@@NT          @I@@@@          LA        12,BRANIC(1,1).                   OB
)@@G@@                              @I@@@@          J         *BRANIC(1,2),12.OC
)@@G@@                                                @I@@@@          END.    OD
)@@G@@                                                                  @I@@@@OE

)@@G@@6 , + '      '.                                                   @I@@@@OJ
)@@G@@          END.                                                          OK

)@@G@@***********************CHKVAL**JC00             @I@@@@CHKVAL**  PROC    ON
)@@G@@  1.                 CHECK VALUE                                  @I@@@@OO
)@@G@@GT        EQU       CHKVAL(1,*4).                                       OP
)@@G@@            @I@@@@EQ        EQU       CHKVAL(1,*5).                     OQ
)@@G@@                              @I@@@@LT        EQU       CHKVAL(1,*6).   OR
)@@G@@                                                @I@@@@  DO LT ,  LA   A0OS
)@@G@@,CHKVAL(1,3)+3.                                                   @I@@@@OT
)@@G@@  DO LT , AA        A0,CHKVAL(1,2).                                     OU
)@@G@@            @I@@@@  DO LT , ANA       A0,CHKVAL(1,1).                   OV
)@@G@@                              @I@@@@  DO 1-LT , LA      A0,CHKVAL(1,1). OW
)@@G@@                                                @I@@@@  DO 1-LT , ANA   OX
)@@G@@  A0,CHKVAL(1,3)+3.                                               @I@@@@OY
)@@G@@  DO 1-LT , ANA     A0,CHKVAL(1,2).                                     OZ
)@@G@@            @G@@@[          JO        AERROR.        TEST FOR OVERFLOW. PA
)@@G@@             JC12 @I@@@@           JZ    A0,EQEXIT.                     PB
)@@G@@                                    @I@@@@  DO  1-(LT**GT) ,  JP    A0,CPC
)@@G@@HKVAL(1,6-2*LT).                                      @I@@@@  DO 1-(LT++PD
)@@G@@GT) , J CHKVAL(1,4).                                                    PE
)@@G@@@I@@@@EQEXIT    LOCC      CHKVAL(1,5),$.                                PF
)@@G@@ JC02             @I@@@@          END.                                  PG
)@@G@@                                    @I@@@@. ****************************PH

)@@G@@***********************************************CLERTB**JC00             PJ

)@@G@@X TABLE 'TABLE' ARE SET TO THE TAG 'KJC30             @I@@@@. IF KEY = CPN

)@@G@@ JC30             @I@@@@.                                               PQ

)@@G@@                                    @I@@@@. BEGIN FRWDTB                OL
)@@G@@                                                      @I@@@@. FOR(BLANK)OM
)@@G@@ CONTIN                                                                 ON
)@@G@@@I@@@@. FOR(EQUAL) PUT(EQTYP) STOP                                      OO
)@@G@@                  @I@@@@. FOR(RIGHTPAREN) PUT(RPTYP) STOP               OP
)@@G@@                                    @I@@@@. FOR(RIGHTBR) PUT(RBTYP) STOPOQ
)@@G@@                                                      @I@@@@. FOR(COMMA)OR
)@@G@@ PUT(CMATYP) STOP                                                       OS
)@@G@@@I@@@@. FOR(COLON) PUT(CLNTYP) STOP                                     OT
)@@G@@                  @I@@@@. FOR(EOS) PUT(EOSTYP) STOP                     OU
)@@G@@                                    @I@@@@. ELSE PUT(NBTYP) STOPSH      OV
)@@G@@                                                      @I@@@@. END FRWDTBOW
)@@G@@                                                                        OX

)@@G@@@I@@@@. FOR(STAR) PUT(STRFN) GOTO(NBLKTB)                               NN
)@@G@@                  @I@@@@. FOR(SLASH) PUT(SLHFN) GOTO(NBLKTB)            NO
)@@G@@                                    @I@@@@. FOR(PERCENT) PUT(PRFN) GOTO(NP
)@@G@@NBLKTB)                                               @I@@@@. FOR(AT) PUNQ
)@@G@@T(ATFN) GOTO(NBLKTB)                                                    NR
)@@G@@@I@@@@. FOR(POUND) PUT(PDFN) GOTO(NBLKTB)                               NS
)@@G@@                  @I@@@@. FOR(KEYSYM) PUT(KEYFN) GOTO(NBLKTB)           NT
)@@G@@                                    @I@@@@. FOR(NOTSYM) PUT(NEGFN) GOTO(NU
)@@G@@NBLKTB)                                               @I@@@@. FOR(ORSYM)NV
)@@G@@ PUT(BARFN) GOTO(NBLKTB)                                                NW
)@@G@@@I@@@@. FOR(QUESYM) PUT(QUESFN) GOTO(NBLKTB)                            NX
)@@G@@                  @I@@@@. FOR(RAISE) PUT(AROWFN) GOTO(NBLKTB)           NY
)@@G@@                                    @I@@@@. ELSE ERROR                  NZ
)@@G@@                                                      @I@@@@. END UNOPTBOA

)@@G@@@I@@@@          SYNVEC    VARTB,*0.                     .               BJ
)@@G@@                  @I@@@@          SYNVEC    *ERROR,*0.                  BK
)@@G@@  "                                 @I@@@@          SYNVEC    *ERROR,*0.BL
)@@G@@                    _                                 @I@@@@.           BM
)@@G@@                                                                        BN
)@@G@@@I@@@@          END.      COPYMDATA.                                    BO

)@@G@@*JC00             @I@@@@. APDSPS IS THE SUBROUTINE FOR THE APDSP ('APPENBZ
)@@G@@D SPECIFIER')      JC04             @I@@@@. COMMAND.  THE CALL OF:      CA
)@@G@@                                     JC04             @I@@@@.         APCB
)@@G@@DSP     S1,S2.                                         JC04             CC
)@@G@@@I@@@@. IS EXPANDED INTO:                                               CD
)@@G@@ JC04             @I@@@@.         LX,U      X2,S1.                      CE
)@@G@@                   JC04             @I@@@@.         LX,U      X3,S2.    CF
)@@G@@                                     JC04             @I@@@@.         LMCG
)@@G@@J       A11,APDSPS.                                    JC04             CH
)@@G@@@I@@@@.                                                                 CI
)@@G@@ JC04             @I@@@@. SEE THE MACRO MANUAL FOR A COMPLETE DESCRIPTIOCJ
)@@G@@N OF THIS INSTRUCTIJC04             @I@@@@. BASICALLY, THE STRING S2 IS CK
)@@G@@COPIED INTO THE SPACE IMMEDIATELY AFTJC04             @I@@@@. THE STRINGCL
)@@G@@ S1.  BEFORE THIS IS CALLED, CARE MUST BE TAKEN TO ENSUJC04             CM
)@@G@@@I@@@@. THAT THERE IS ROOM AFTER S1 FOR THE STRING--NO CHECK IS (OR CAN CN
)@@G@@BJC04             @I@@@@. MADE HERE.  S1 WILL ALSO HAVE ITS LENGTH INCRECO
)@@G@@ASED TO L(S1)+L(S2)JC04             @I@@@@. MAKING THE NEW CHARACTERS A CP
)@@G@@PART OF S1.                          JC04             @I@@@@.    A SPECICQ
)@@G@@AL COMMENT OF THE O-FIELD IS IN ORDER HERE.  THE 'OFFSEJC04             CR
)@@G@@@I@@@@. FIELD IS STORED AS A WHOLE WORD, THE 3RD WORD OF A SPECIFIER,   CS
)@@G@@ JC04             @I@@@@. AND IS MADE UP OF TWO INTEGERS, A 'WORD' AND 'CT
)@@G@@CHARACTER' PART.   JC04             @I@@@@. THUS, FOR A SPECIFIER S,    CU
)@@G@@                                     JC04             @I@@@@.    H2(S+2)CV
)@@G@@+S = WORD CONTAINING FIRST CHARACTER OF STRING;        JC04             CW
)@@G@@@I@@@@.    H1(S+2) = CHARACTER WITHIN WORD (<6).                        CX
)@@G@@ JC04             @I@@@@.                                               CY
)@@G@@                   JC04             @I@@@@. THIS ISN'T LIMITED TO 64K.  CZ
)@@G@@                                     JC04             @I@@@@. X1-X3, A0-DA
)@@G@@A5 ARE USED.                                           JC04             DB
)@@G@@@I@@@@.                                                                 DC
)@@G@@ JC04             @I@@@@APDSPS*.                                        DD
)@@G@@                   JC04             @I@@@@          LA        A0,3,X2.  DE
)@@G@@L(S1) := A1 := (A0:=L(S1))+S(S2);    JC04             @I@@@@          AUDF
)@@G@@        A0,3,X3.  (INCREMENT LENGTH OF S1.)            JC04             DG
)@@G@@@I@@@@          SA        A1,3,X2.  '                                   DH
)@@G@@ JC04             @I@@@@.                                               DI
)@@G@@                   JC04             @I@@@@          AA,H1     A0,2,X2.  DJ
)@@G@@THE WORD TO START COPYING TO IS:     JC04             @I@@@@          DSDK
)@@G@@L       A0,36.       A0 = A(S1)+H2(O(S1))+(H1(O(S1))   JC04             DL
)@@G@@@I@@@@          DI,U      A0,6.                        +L(S1))/6.       DM
)@@G@@ JC04             @I@@@@          AA,H2     A0,2,X2.  THE CHAR WITHIN THDN
)@@G@@IS WORD IS:        JC04             @I@@@@          AA        A0,0,X2.  DO
)@@G@@   A1 = REM(L(S1)+H1(O(S1)),6).      JC04             @I@@@@.           DP
)@@G@@                                                       JC04             DQ
)@@G@@@I@@@@          LA,H2     A2,2,X3.  THE WORD TO START COPYING FROM IS:  DR
)@@G@@ JC04             @I@@@@          AA        A2,0,X3.     A2 = A(S2)+H2(ODS
)@@G@@(S2)).             JC04             @I@@@@          LA,H1     A3,2,X3.  DT
)@@G@@THE CHAR WITHIN THIS WORD IS:        JC04             @I@@@@.           DU
)@@G@@                     A3 = H1(O(S2)).                   JC04             DV
)@@G@@@I@@@@          LXI,U     A0,1.     SET INCREMENTS TO 1.                DW
)@@G@@ JC04             @I@@@@          LXI,U     A1,1.     '                 DX
)@@G@@                   JC04             @I@@@@          LXI,U     A2,1.     DY
)@@G@@'                                    JC04             @I@@@@          LXDZ
)@@G@@I,U     A3,1.     '                                    JC04             EA
)@@G@@@I@@@@          LA        A5,3,X3.  LENGTH OF STRING TO COPY--LOOP CONTREB
)@@G@@OJC04             @I@@@@          J         APDSPY.                     EC
)@@G@@                   JC04             @I@@@@APDSPX    EX        CHRLA4,*A3ED
)@@G@@.    GET A CHAR OF S1.               JC04             @I@@@@          EXEE
)@@G@@        CHRSA4,*A1.    MOVE IT TO S2.                  JC04             EF
)@@G@@@I@@@@APDSPY    JGD       A5,APDSPX.     IF (A5:=A5-1) >= 0, REPEAT.    EG
)@@G@@ JC04             @I@@@@          J         0,X11.    RETURN.           EH
)@@G@@                   JC04             @I@@@@. ****************************EI
)@@G@@*****************************APDSPS**JC00             @I@@@@. **********EJ
)@@G@@***********************************************CHR TABLJC30             EK
)@@G@@@I@@@@CHRLA5*.                           LOAD A CHARACTER INTO A5, CALLEEL
)@@G@@DJC11             @I@@@@          LA,S1     A5,0,X2.            EX   CHREM
