)@@G@@*****************************LEXCMPS*JC04*@G@@[]. LEXCMPS IS THE LEXCMP IU
)@@G@@SUBROUTINE.  IT IS INVOKED BY:             JC04 @G@@[].         LEXCMP  IV
)@@G@@  S1,S2,GT,EQ,LT.                                JC04 @G@@[]. WHICH IS EIW
)@@G@@XPANDED TO:                                            JC04 @G@@[].     IX
)@@G@@    LX,U      X7,S1.                                         JC04 @G@@[]IY
)@@G@@.         LX,U      X8,S2.                                         JC04 IZ
)@@G@@@G@@[].         LX,U      X9,GT.                                        JA
)@@G@@ JC04 @G@@[].         LX,U      X10,EQ.                                 JB
)@@G@@       JC04 @G@@[].         LX,U      X11,LT.                           JC
)@@G@@             JC04 @G@@[].         J         LEXCMPS.                    JD
)@@G@@                   JC04 @G@@[].                                         JE
)@@G@@                         JC04 @G@@[]LEXCMPS*.                           JF
)@@G@@                               JC04 @G@@[]          LA        A6,3,X7.  JG
)@@G@@A6  =  L(S1)                         JC04 @G@@[]          ANU       A6,3JH
)@@G@@,X8.  A7 = L(S1) - L(S2)                   JC04 @G@@[]          LA      JI
)@@G@@  A8,X11.   DOES GT = LT?                        JC04 @G@@[]          TNJJ
)@@G@@E       A8,X9.    IF SO, THIS IS EQ/NE TEST--          JC04 @G@@[]      JK
)@@G@@    JNZ       A7,0,X11. IF LENGTHS DIFFER, TAKE NE EXIT.     JC04 @G@@[]JL
)@@G@@          TN        A7.       OTHERWISE, IF L(S1) > L(S2),         JC04 JM
)@@G@@@G@@[]          LA        A6,3,X8.  USE L(S2) FOR LOOP CONTROL.         JN
)@@G@@ JC04 @G@@[].                             SET UP POINTERS TO STRINGS:   JO
)@@G@@       JC04 @G@@[]          LA        A2,0,X7.  A(S1)                   JP
)@@G@@             JC04 @G@@[]          AA,H2     A2,2,X7.  + OW(S1)          JQ
)@@G@@                   JC04 @G@@[]          LA,H1     A3,2,X7.  OC(S1)      JR
)@@G@@                         JC04 @G@@[]          LA        A0,0,X8.  A(S2) JS
)@@G@@                               JC04 @G@@[]          AA,H2     A0,2,X8.  JT
)@@G@@+ OW(S2)                             JC04 @G@@[]          LA,H1     A1,2JU
)@@G@@,X8.  OC(S2)                               JC04 @G@@[]          LXI,U   JV
)@@G@@  A0,1.     INCREMENTS = 1                       JC04 @G@@[]          LXJW
)@@G@@I,U     A1,1.                                          JC04 @G@@[]      JX
)@@G@@    LXI,U     A2,1.                                          JC04 @G@@[]JY
)@@G@@          LXI,U     A3,1.                                          JC04 JZ
)@@G@@@G@@[].                                                                 KA
)@@G@@ JC04 @G@@[]          J         $+3.      COMPARE THE TWO STRINGS:      KB
)@@G@@       JC04 @G@@[]LEXCMPT   EX        CHRLA4,*A3.    GET A CHAR FROM S1.KC
)@@G@@             JC04 @G@@[]          EX        CHTNE$,*A1.    IS IT EQUAL TKD
)@@G@@O THE ONE IN S2?   JC04 @G@@[]          JGD       A6,LEXCMPT.    YEP--ANKE
)@@G@@Y MORE LEFT?             JC04 @G@@[]          JN        A6,LEXCMPE.    NKF
)@@G@@E OR OUT OF CHARS--WHICH ONE?  JC04 @G@@[]          EX        CHTLE$-1,AKG
)@@G@@1.   IF NE, IS S1 CHAR LESS?         JC04 @G@@[]          J         0,X1KH
)@@G@@1.    S1 LESS, TAKE LT EXIT.               JC04 @G@@[]          J       KI
)@@G@@  0,X9.     S2 LESS, TAKE GT EXIT.               JC04 @G@@[].           KJ
)@@G@@                                                       JC04 @G@@[]LEXCMPKK
)@@G@@E.                      RAN OUT OF CHARS--COMPARE LENGTHS.   JC04 @G@@[]KL
)@@G@@          JZ        A7,0,X10. IF L(S1) = L(S2), STRINGS ARE EQ.    JC04 KM
)@@G@@@G@@[]          JN        A7,0,X11. IF L(S1) < L(S2), TAKE LT EXIT.     KN
)@@G@@ JC04 @G@@[]          J         0,X9.     OTHERWISE TAKE GT EXIT.       KO
)@@G@@       JC04 @G@@[]. ****************************************************KP
)@@G@@*****LEXCMPS*JC04 @G@@[]. **********************************************KQ
)@@G@@***********LINKS***JC22 @G@@[]. LINKS IS THE SUBROUTINE FOR THE 'LINK' MKR
)@@G@@ACRO.  IT INVOKES AN     JC22 @G@@[]. 'EXTERNAL' FORTRAN SUBROUTINE.  THKS
)@@G@@E LINK MACRO IS CALLED AS:     JC22 @G@@[].         LINK      D1,D2,D3,DKT
)@@G@@4,FAIL,SUCC.                         JC22 @G@@[]. WHICH IS ASSEMBLED ON KU
)@@G@@THE 1108 AS:                               JC22 @G@@[].         LX,U    KV
)@@G@@  X8,D1.    DESCR FOR RETURN VALUE.              JC22 @G@@[].         LXKW
)@@G@@        X9,D2.    ADDR OF ARGUMENT BLOCK.              JC22 @G@@[].     KX
)@@G@@    LX,U      X10,FAIL. FAILURE EXIT.                        JC22 @G@@[]KY
)@@G@@.         LX,U      X11,SUCC. SUCCESS EXIT.                        JC22 KZ
)@@G@@@G@@[].         LA,U      A0,D4.    LOC OF FUNCTION DESCR.              LA
)@@G@@ JC22 @G@@[].         LA        A1,D3.    NUMBER OF ACTUAL ARGUMENTS.   LB
)@@G@@       JC22 @G@@[].         J         LINKS.    CALL THIS ROUTINE.      LC
)@@G@@             JC22 @G@@[].                                               LD
)@@G@@                   JC22 @G@@[]. A FORTRAN CALLING SEQUENCE IS GENERATED LE
)@@G@@FOR THE DESIRED FUNCTION JC22 @G@@[]. AND THE FUNCTION IS THEN TRANSFERRLF
)@@G@@ED TO.  THIS REQUIRES THE      JC22 @G@@[]. TRANSLATING OF SOME DATA TYPLG
)@@G@@ES INTO A FORTRAN-COMPATIBLE FORM.   JC22 @G@@[]. THE CONVERSION ROUTINELH
)@@G@@S ARE DOCUMENTED BELOW, WHERE THEY OCCUR.  JC22 @G@@[]. A NORMAL FORTRANLI
)@@G@@ RETURN WILL CAUSE THE VALUE IN A0 TO BE PUT IN  JC22 @G@@[]. THE RETURNLJ
)@@G@@ LOCATION; ITS TYPE IS ASSUMED TO BE CORRECT.  OTHER   JC22 @G@@[]. RETULK
)@@G@@RN ROUTINES ARE PROVIDED (FRETURN, IRETURN, RRETURN, SRETURN)JC22 @G@@[]LL
)@@G@@. THAT ALLOW MORE SNOBOL-LIKE RETURNS; THEY ARE DOCUMENTED BELOW   JC22 LM
)@@G@@@G@@[]. WHERE THEY OCCUR.                                               LN
)@@G@@ JC22 @G@@[].                                                           LO
)@@G@@       JC22 @G@@[]          LON.                                        LP
)@@G@@             JC10 @G@@[]$(2).                                           LQ
)@@G@@                   JC22 @G@@[]LINKJ     J         LINKRTN.  RETURN INST LR
)@@G@@FOR FORTRAN CALL.        JC22 @G@@[]LINKX5    +         0.        LOCATILS
)@@G@@ONS FOR SAVING REGISTERS PAST  JC22 @G@@[]LINKX6    +         0.        LT
)@@G@@CALL OF THE EXTERNAL ROUTINE.        JC22 @G@@[]LINKX8    +         0.  LU
)@@G@@                                           JC22 @G@@[]LINKX9    +       LV
)@@G@@  0.                                             JC22 @G@@[]LINKX10   + LW
)@@G@@        0.                                             JC22 @G@@[]LINKX1LX
)@@G@@1   +         0.                                             JC22 @G@@[]LY
)@@G@@LINKA0    +         0.                                             JC22 LZ
)@@G@@@G@@[]LINKA1    +         0.                                            MA
)@@G@@ JC22 @G@@[].                                                           MB
)@@G@@       JC22 @G@@[]LINKSX7   +         0.        SPACE FOR SAVING REGISTEMC
)@@G@@RS DURING    JC22 @G@@[]LINKSX9   +         0.        PARAMETER CONVERSIMD
)@@G@@ON.                JC22 @G@@[]LINKSA1   +         0.                    ME
)@@G@@                         JC22 @G@@[].                                   MF
)@@G@@                               JC22 @G@@[]LINKD1    DESCR     *0,*0,*0. MG
)@@G@@     SCRATCH DESCRIPTOR.             JC22 @G@@[]LINKD2    DESCR     *0,*MH
)@@G@@0,*0.                                      JC22 @G@@[]LINKS1    SPEC    MI
)@@G@@  *0,*0,*0,*0,*0.  SCRATCH SPECIFIER.            JC22 @G@@[]LINKS2    SPMJ
)@@G@@EC      *0,*0,*0,*0,*0.                                JC22 @G@@[].     MK
)@@G@@                                                             JC22 @G@@[]ML
)@@G@@$(1).                                                              JC22 MM
)@@G@@@G@@[]LINKS*.                                                           MN
)@@G@@ JC22 @G@@[]          TNZ       0,A0.          IF FUNCTION ADDR = 0,    MO
)@@G@@       JC22 @G@@[]          J         UNDF.             IT ISN'T DEFINEDMP
)@@G@@.            JC22 @G@@[]          TE,H2     A1,1,A0.       CORRECT NUMBEMQ
)@@G@@R OF ARGS?         JC22 @G@@[]          J         ARGNER.        NO--ERRMR
)@@G@@OR FOR NOW.              JC22 @G@@[]          TG,U      A1,EXPMAX+1.   CMS
)@@G@@AN WE HANDLE THIS MANY?        JC22 @G@@[]          J         TOOMANYARGMT
)@@G@@S.   IF NOT, ERROR.                  JC22 @G@@[]          LXI,U     X9,2MU
)@@G@@.          INCREMENT FOR ACCESSING PARAMS. JC22 @G@@[]          SX      MV
)@@G@@  X5,LINKX5.     SAVE REGISTERS.                 JC22 @G@@[]          SXMW
)@@G@@        X6,LINKX6.                                     JC22 @G@@[]      MX
)@@G@@    SX        X8,LINKX8.                                     JC22 @G@@[]MY
)@@G@@          SX        X9,LINKX9.                                     JC22 MZ
)@@G@@@G@@[]          SX        X10,LINKX10.                                  NA
)@@G@@ JC22 @G@@[]          SX        X11,LINKX11.                            NB
)@@G@@       JC22 @G@@[]          SA        A0,LINKA0.                        NC
)@@G@@             JC22 @G@@[]          SA        A1,LINKA1.                  ND
)@@G@@                   JC22 @G@@[]          LX        X7,(1,0).      COUNTERNE
)@@G@@ FOR PARAMS COPIED.      JC22 @G@@[]          J         LINKT.         GNF
)@@G@@O TRANSLATE PARAMETERS.        JC22 @G@@[].                             NG
)@@G@@                                     JC22 @G@@[]. THE FOLLOWING CODE TRANH
)@@G@@NSLATES THE PARAMETERS FROM THEIR SNOBOL4  JC22 @G@@[]. FORMS TO FORTRANNI
)@@G@@ FORMS.  THIS CODE USES X7, X9 AND A1, SO THE    JC22 @G@@[]. CONVERSIONNJ
)@@G@@ ROUTINES MUST NOT DESTROY THEM.                       JC22 @G@@[].     NK
)@@G@@                                                             JC22 @G@@[]NL
)@@G@@LINKP     LA,H2     A2,1,X9.       GET TYPE OF THIS PARAM.         JC22 NM
)@@G@@@G@@[]          TNE,U     A2,INTDT.      TEST ITS TYPE:                 NN
)@@G@@ JC22 @G@@[]          J         LINKPOK.       INTEGER--NO CHANGE.      NO
)@@G@@       JC22 @G@@[]          TNE,U     A2,REALDT.                        NP
)@@G@@             JC22 @G@@[]          J         LINKPOK.       REAL--NO CHANNQ
)@@G@@GE.                JC22 @G@@[]          TNE,U     A2,STRDT.             NR
)@@G@@                         JC22 @G@@[]          J         LINKSSF.       SNS
)@@G@@TRING--CONVERT.                JC22 @G@@[]          J         INTR1.    NT
)@@G@@     CAN'T HANDLE OTHER TYPES.       JC22 @G@@[].                       NU
)@@G@@                                           JC22 @G@@[]LINKPOK.          NV
)@@G@@                 NO CHANGE NEEDED--STORE ITS     JC22 @G@@[]          SXNW
)@@G@@,H2     X9,LINKCALL,X7.   ADDRESS IN CALLING SEQUENCE. JC22 @G@@[]      NX
)@@G@@    SZ,H1     LINKCALL,*X7.  UPDATE TO NEXT LOCATION.        JC22 @G@@[]NY
)@@G@@          LA,U      A2,0,*X9.      UPDATE POINTER TO NEXT PARAM.   JC22 NZ
)@@G@@@G@@[]LINKT     JGD       A1,LINKP.      IF ANY MORE PARAMS, REPEAT.    OA
)@@G@@ JC22 @G@@[].                                                           OB
)@@G@@       JC22 @G@@[]. ALL THE PARAMS ARE CONVERTED; INSERT A DUMMY WALKBACOC
)@@G@@K WORD AND   JC22 @G@@[]. A JUMP TO THE RETURN CODE BELOW, AND TRANSFER OD
)@@G@@TO THE FUNCTION.   JC22 @G@@[].                                         OE
)@@G@@                         JC22 @G@@[]          SZ        LINKCALL,*X7.  ZOF
)@@G@@ERO FOR WALKBACK WORD.         JC22 @G@@[]          LA        A2,LINKJ. OG
)@@G@@     GET JUMP INST TO RETURN CODE.   JC22 @G@@[]          SA        A2,LOH
)@@G@@INKCALL,X7.     PUT IT AT RETURN LOC.      JC22 @G@@[].                 OI
)@@G@@                                                 JC22 @G@@[]          LXOJ
)@@G@@,U      X11,LINKCALL.  X11 = ADDR OF 1ST PARAM.        JC22 @G@@[]      OK
)@@G@@    LA        A0,LINKA0.     GET LOC OF FCT DESCR.           JC22 @G@@[]OL
)@@G@@          LA        A0,0,A0.       GET FUNCTION ADDRESS.           JC22 OM
)@@G@@@G@@[]          J         0,A0.          CALL THE FUNCTION.             ON
)@@G@@ JC22 @G@@[].                                                           OO
)@@G@@       JC22 @G@@[]LINKCALL  RES       27.            SPACE FOR PARAMS, WOP
)@@G@@ALKBACK, AND JC22 @G@@[].                                  RETURN INSTRUOQ
)@@G@@CTION.             JC22 @G@@[].                                         OR
)@@G@@                         JC22 @G@@[].                                  ROS
)@@G@@ETURN CODE:                    JC22 @G@@[]LINKRTN   LA,U      A3,2.     OT
)@@G@@     RETURN INDICATOR = 'NORMAL'.    JC22 @G@@[]          LX        X8,LOU
)@@G@@INKX8.     GET ADDR FOR RETURN VALUE.      JC22 @G@@[]          SA      OV
)@@G@@  A0,0,X8.       STORE VALUE RETURNED IN A-FIELD.JC22 @G@@[]LINKRR.     OW
)@@G@@                       ENTRY HERE FROM OTHER RETURNS.  JC22 @G@@[]      OX
)@@G@@    LX        X5,LINKX5.     RESTORE REGISTERS.              JC22 @G@@[]OY
)@@G@@          LX        X6,LINKX6.                                     JC22 OZ
)@@G@@@G@@[]          LX        X9,LINKX9.                                    PA
)@@G@@ JC22 @G@@[]          LX        X10,LINKX10.                            PB
)@@G@@       JC22 @G@@[]          LX        X11,LINKX11.                      PC
)@@G@@             JC22 @G@@[]          LA        A0,LINKA0.                  PD
)@@G@@                   JC22 @G@@[]          LA        A1,LINKA1.            PE
)@@G@@                         JC22 @G@@[]          J         LINKRT.        GPF
)@@G@@O RE-CONVERT PARAMS.           JC22 @G@@[].                             PG
)@@G@@                                     JC22 @G@@[]. THE FOLLOWING CODE RE-PH
)@@G@@CONVERTS ANY PARAMETERS BACK TO SNOBOL4    JC22 @G@@[]. FORM.  IT IS ONLPI
)@@G@@Y NECESSARY CURRENTLY FOR ARRAYS, SINCE THERE    JC22 @G@@[]. IS CURRENTPJ
)@@G@@LY NO WAY TO GET CALL-BY-NAME PARAMETERS.              JC22 @G@@[].     PK
)@@G@@                                                             JC22 @G@@[]PL
)@@G@@LINKRP    LA,H2     A2,1,X9.       GET TYPE OF PARAM.              JC22 PM
)@@G@@@G@@[]          TNE,U     A2,INTDT.      TEST ITS TYPE:                 PN
)@@G@@ JC22 @G@@[]          J         LINKROK.       INTEGER--NO CHANGE.      PO
)@@G@@       JC22 @G@@[]          TNE,U     A2,REALDT.                        PP
)@@G@@             JC22 @G@@[]          J         LINKROK.       REAL--NO CHANPQ
)@@G@@GE.                JC22 @G@@[]          TNE,U     A2,STRDT.             PR
)@@G@@                         JC22 @G@@[]          J         LINKROK.       SPS
)@@G@@TRING--FORGET IT.              JC22 @G@@[].                             PT
)@@G@@     IF ANY OTHER TYPE, DON'T BOTHER JC22 @G@@[].                       PU
)@@G@@                                           JC22 @G@@[]LINKROK   LA,U    PV
)@@G@@  A2,0,*X9.      UPDATE POINTER TO NEXT PARAM.   JC22 @G@@[]LINKRT    JGPW
)@@G@@D       A1,LINKRP.     IF MORE PARAMS, REPEAT.         JC22 @G@@[]      PX
)@@G@@    J         $,A3.          IF NOT, TAKE APPROPRIATE RETURN JC22 @G@@[]PY
)@@G@@          J         0,X10.         1 = FRETURN.                    JC22 PZ
)@@G@@@G@@[]          J         0,X11.         2 = NORMAL FORTRAN RETURN.     QA
)@@G@@ JC22 @G@@[]          J         0,X11.         3 = SRETURN.             QB
)@@G@@       JC22 @G@@[]          J         0,X11.         4 = IRETURN.       QC
)@@G@@             JC22 @G@@[]          J         0,X11.         5 = RRETURN. QD
)@@G@@                   JC22 @G@@[].                                         QE
)@@G@@                         JC22 @G@@[]. LINKSSF CONVERTS A SNOBOL4 STRING QF
)@@G@@TO ONE USABLE BY FORTRAN.      JC22 @G@@[]. THIS IS AN ARRAY, S(I), IN WQG
)@@G@@HICH S(1) IS THE SIZE OF THE STRING  JC22 @G@@[]. (IN CHARACTERS), AND SQH
)@@G@@(2), S(3), ... HOLD THE STRING IN THE      JC22 @G@@[]. 'HOLLERITH' FORMQI
)@@G@@AT, 6 CHARACTERS PER WORD ON THE 1108.  A        JC22 @G@@[]. STRING PASQJ
)@@G@@SED TO A FORTRAN ROUTINE IS IN A TEMPORARY BLOCK OF    JC22 @G@@[]. MEMOQK
)@@G@@RY, SO THE ROUTINE CAN ALTER IT IF IT WANTS TOO--BUT IT HAD  JC22 @G@@[]QL
)@@G@@. BETTER NOT TRY WRITING BEYOND THE LAST WORD ALLOCATED, OR        JC22 QM
)@@G@@@G@@[]. SOME STRANGE THINGS MAY HAPPEN AFTER THE RETURN.                QN
)@@G@@ JC22 @G@@[].                                                           QO
)@@G@@       JC22 @G@@[]LINKSSF.                                              QP
)@@G@@             JC22 @G@@[]          SX        X7,LINKSX7.    SAVE REGISTERQQ
)@@G@@S:                 JC22 @G@@[]          SX        X9,LINKSX9.           QR
)@@G@@                         JC22 @G@@[]          SA        A1,LINKSA1.     QS
)@@G@@                               JC22 @G@@[]          DL        A2,0,X9.  QT
)@@G@@     MAKE A LOCAL DESCRIPTOR FOR IT. JC22 @G@@[]          DS        A2,LQU
)@@G@@INKD1.                                     JC22 @G@@[]          LOCSP   QV
)@@G@@  LINKS1,LINKD1. GET A SPECIFIER FOR THE STRING. JC22 @G@@[]          GEQW
)@@G@@TLG     LINKD1,LINKS1. GET ITS SPACE REQUIREMENTS.     JC22 @G@@[]      QX
)@@G@@    RCALL     LINKD2,CONVAR LINKD1 *0.                       JC22 @G@@[]QY
)@@G@@.                                  ALLOCATE A BLOCK OF STORAGE.    JC22 QZ
)@@G@@@G@@[]          LOCSP     LINKS2,LINKD2. GET A SPECIFIER FOR NEW STRING.RA
)@@G@@ JC22 @G@@[]          SETLC     LINKS2,*0.     SET IT TO NULL.          RB
)@@G@@       JC22 @G@@[]          APDSP     LINKS2,LINKS1. COPY OLD STRING TO RC
)@@G@@NEW BLOCK.   JC22 @G@@[]          LA        A2,LINKS2.     ADDR OF NEW SRD
)@@G@@TRING BLOCK.       JC22 @G@@[]          AA,U      A2,7.          MOVE TORE
)@@G@@ WORD BEFORE STRING.     JC22 @G@@[]          LA,H2     A3,LINKS2+3.   GRF
)@@G@@ET LENGTH OF STRING.           JC22 @G@@[]          SA        A3,0,A2.  RG
)@@G@@     PUT INTO WORD BEFORE STRING.    JC22 @G@@[]          LX        X7,LRH
)@@G@@INKSX7.    RESTORE REGISTERS:              JC22 @G@@[]          LX      RI
)@@G@@  X9,LINKSX9.                                    JC22 @G@@[]          LARJ
)@@G@@        A1,LINKSA1.                                    JC22 @G@@[]      RK
)@@G@@    SA,H2     A2,LINKCALL,X7. PUT ADDR INTO CALLING SEQ.     JC22 @G@@[]RL
)@@G@@          SZ,H1     LINKCALL,*X7.  UPDATE TO NEXT LOC.             JC22 RM
)@@G@@@G@@[]          DL        A3,LINKD2.     PUT DESCR OF NEW BLOCK INTO    RN
)@@G@@ JC22 @G@@[]          DS        A3,0,*X9.      PARAM LIST, SO G.C. WILL RO
)@@G@@LEAVE  JC22 @G@@[].                                  IT ALONE.          RP
)@@G@@             JC22 @G@@[]          J         LINKT.         GO GET NEXT PRQ
)@@G@@ARAM.              JC22 @G@@[]. ****************************************RR
)@@G@@*****************LINKS***JC22 @G@@[]. **********************************RS
)@@G@@***********************LOADS***JC22 @G@@[].                             RT
)@@G@@                                     JC22 @G@@[]$(2).                   RU
)@@G@@                                           JC22 @G@@[]LOADSP1   SPEC    RV
)@@G@@  *0,*0,*0,*0,*0.     SCRATCH SPECIFIER.         JC22 @G@@[]LOADSP2   SPRW
)@@G@@EC      LOADST,*0,*0,*0,*0. SPECIFIER FOR NAME:        JC22 @G@@[]LOADSTRX
)@@G@@    +         '      '.           NAME OF FUNCTION.          JC22 @G@@[]RY
)@@G@@LOADSX11  +         0.                  FOR SAVING X11.            JC22 RZ
)@@G@@@G@@[].                                                                 SA
)@@G@@ JC22 @G@@[]$(1).                                                       SB
)@@G@@       JC22 @G@@[]LOADS*.                                               SC
)@@G@@             JC22 @G@@[]          LA,U      A0,EXTERNAL.   DOES FCT TABLSD
)@@G@@E EXIST?           JC22 @G@@[]          JZ        A0,0,X10.      IF NOT,SE
)@@G@@ FAIL.                   JC22 @G@@[]          DL        A0,0,X9.       CSF
)@@G@@OPY AFV(S1) TO LOADSP1.        JC22 @G@@[]          DS        A0,LOADSP1SG
)@@G@@.                                    JC22 @G@@[]          LA,H2     A1,3SH
)@@G@@,X9.       L(S1)                           JC22 @G@@[]          LA      SI
)@@G@@  A0,2,X9.       O(S1)                           JC22 @G@@[]          TGSJ
)@@G@@,U      A1,7.          IF L(S1) >= 7,                  JC22 @G@@[]      SK
)@@G@@    LA,U      A1,6.             SET L(S1) TO 6.              JC22 @G@@[]SL
)@@G@@          DS        A0,LOADSP1+2   PUT OL(S1) IN LOADSP1.          JC22 SM
)@@G@@@G@@[]          SZ        LOADSP2+2.     O(LOADSP2) = 0.                SN
)@@G@@ JC22 @G@@[]          SZ        LOADSP2+3.     L(LOADSP2) = 0.          SO
)@@G@@       JC22 @G@@[]          LA        A0,('      '). SET LOADST TO BLANKSP
)@@G@@S.           JC22 @G@@[]          SA        A0,LOADST.                  SQ
)@@G@@                   JC22 @G@@[]          SX        X11,LOADSX11.  SAVE RESR
)@@G@@TURN LOC.                JC22 @G@@[]          APDSP     LOADSP2,LOADSP1.SS
)@@G@@    COPY UP TO 6 CHARS OF NAME JC22 @G@@[]          LX        X11,LOADSXST
)@@G@@11.  RESTORE RETURN LOC.             JC22 @G@@[]          LA        A0,LSU
)@@G@@OADST.     A0 = FCT NAME.                  JC22 @G@@[]          LA      SV
)@@G@@  A1,(2,EXTERNAL).    LOCATION OF FCT TABLE.     JC22 @G@@[]LOADT     TNSW
)@@G@@E       A0,0,A1.       TEST NAME AGAINST TABLE ENTRY.  JC22 @G@@[]      SX
)@@G@@    J         LOADIT.        IF EQUAL, GO TO LOADING CODE.   JC22 @G@@[]SY
)@@G@@          TNZ       0,*A1.         IF ZERO ENTRY,                  JC22 SZ
)@@G@@@G@@[]          J         0,X10.            END OF TABLE--FAIL.         TA
)@@G@@ JC22 @G@@[]          J         LOADT.         OTHERWISE TRY NEXT ENTRY.TB
)@@G@@       JC22 @G@@[].                                                     TC
)@@G@@             JC22 @G@@[]LOADIT.                            LOAD FUNCTIONTD
)@@G@@ DEFINITION:       JC22 @G@@[]          LA,H2     A2,1,A1.       GET ADDTE
)@@G@@RESS OF FUNCTION.        JC22 @G@@[]          LA,H1     A3,1,A1.       ATF
)@@G@@ND NUMBER OF ARGS.             JC22 @G@@[]          DS        A2,0,X8.  TG
)@@G@@     PUT THEM IN RETURN LOCATION.    JC22 @G@@[]          J         0,X1TH
)@@G@@1.         TAKE SUCCESS EXIT.              JC22 @G@@[]. ****************TI
)@@G@@*****************************************LOADS***JC22 @G@@[]. **********TJ
)@@G@@***********************************************RTNF****JC22 @G@@[].     TK
)@@G@@    CALL  RTNF                                               JC22 @G@@[]TL
)@@G@@.                                                                  JC22 TM
)@@G@@@G@@[]. THIS FORTRAN STATEMENT CAUSES AN EXTERNAL FUNCTION TO FAIL.  IT TN
)@@G@@ JC22 @G@@[]. CAUSES IMMEDIATE RETURN NO MATTER HOW DEEP WITHIN FUNCTIONTO
)@@G@@ CALLS JC22 @G@@[]. THE EXTERNAL FUNCTION IS.  SEE ALSO RTNI.           TP
)@@G@@             JC22 @G@@[].                                               TQ
)@@G@@                   JC22 @G@@[]RTNF**.                                   TR
)@@G@@                         JC22 @G@@[]          LA,U      A3,1.     SET RETS
)@@G@@TURN-TYPE INDICATOR.           JC22 @G@@[]          J         LINKRR.   TT
)@@G@@JOIN RETURN CODE WITHIN LINK ROUTINE JC22 @G@@[]. **********************TU
)@@G@@***********************************RTNF****JC22 @G@@[]. ****************TV
)@@G@@*****************************************RTNI****JC22 @G@@[].         CATW
)@@G@@LL  RTNI(I)                                            JC22 @G@@[].     TX
)@@G@@                                                             JC22 @G@@[]TY
)@@G@@. THIS FORTRAN STATEMENT CAUSES AN EXTERNAL FUNCTION CALLED FROM   JC22 TZ
)@@G@@@G@@[]. A SNOBOL4 PROGRAM TO RETURN THE INTEGER I, NO MATTER WHAT SNOBOLUA
)@@G@@ JC22 @G@@[]. EXPECTED IT TO RETURN.  ALSO, IT FORCES A RETURN TO THE CAUB
)@@G@@LLING  JC22 @G@@[]. SNOBOL STATEMENT NO MATTER HOW DEEP THE PROGRAM IS IUC
)@@G@@N NESTED     JC22 @G@@[]. FORTRAN FUNCTIONS.  THIS IS BECAUSE THE SNOBOLUD
)@@G@@ SYSTEM DOESN'T    JC22 @G@@[]. KNOW ANYTHING ABOUT THE FORTRAN FUNCTIONUE
)@@G@@ CALLS THAT MAY HAVE     JC22 @G@@[]. OCCURRED, AND DOESN'T KNOW HOW TO UF
)@@G@@SIMULATE A FORTRAN RETURN.     JC22 @G@@[]. THIS FEATURE IS ALSO SHARED UG
)@@G@@BY THE OTHER RETURN FUNCTIONS THAT   JC22 @G@@[]. CAUSE A RETURN FROM FOUH
)@@G@@RTRAN TO SNOBOL, SUCH AS RTNF, RTNR, OR    JC22 @G@@[]. RTNS.           UI
)@@G@@                                                 JC22 @G@@[].           UJ
)@@G@@                                                       JC22 @G@@[]RTNI**UK
)@@G@@.                                                            JC22 @G@@[]UL
)@@G@@          LA,U      A3,4.     RETURN-TYPE INDICATOR.               JC22 UM
)@@G@@@G@@[]          LA        A0,0,X11. GET ADDR OF I.                      UN
)@@G@@ JC22 @G@@[]          LA        A0,0,A0.  GET I.                        UO
)@@G@@       JC22 @G@@[]          LA,U      A1,INTDT. GET INTEGER TYPE-CODE.  UP
)@@G@@             JC22 @G@@[]          LX        X8,LINKX8.     GET ADDR FOR UQ
)@@G@@RETURN VALUE.      JC22 @G@@[]          DS        A0,0,X8.  STORE I IN RUR
)@@G@@ETURN LOC.               JC22 @G@@[]          J         LINKRR.   JOIN RUS
)@@G@@ETURN CODE IN LINK ROUTINE.    JC22 @G@@[]. ****************************UT
)@@G@@*****************************RTNI****JC22 @G@@[]. **********************UU
)@@G@@***********************************RTNR****JC22 @G@@[].         CALL  RTUV
)@@G@@NR(R)                                            JC22 @G@@[].           UW
)@@G@@                                                       JC22 @G@@[]. THISUX
)@@G@@ FORTRAN STATEMENT CAUSES AN EXTERNAL FUNCTION TO RETURN THE JC22 @G@@[]UY
)@@G@@. REAL NUMBER R, NO MATTER WHAT SNOBOL4 EXPECTED IT TO RETURN.     JC22 UZ
)@@G@@@G@@[]. SEE ALSO THE ROUTINE RTNI.                                      VA
)@@G@@ JC22 @G@@[].                                                           VB
)@@G@@       JC22 @G@@[]RTNR**.                                               VC
)@@G@@             JC22 @G@@[]          LA,U      A3,5.     RETURN-TYPE INDICAVD
)@@G@@TOR.               JC22 @G@@[]          LA        A0,0,X11. GET ADDR OF VE
)@@G@@R.                       JC22 @G@@[]          LA        A0,0,A0.  GET R.VF
)@@G@@                               JC22 @G@@[]          LA,U      A1,REALDT.VG
)@@G@@     REAL TYPE-CODE.                 JC22 @G@@[]          LX        X8,LVH
)@@G@@INKX8.     ADDR FOR RETURN VALUE.          JC22 @G@@[]          DS      VI
)@@G@@  A0,0,X8.  STORE R IN RETURN LOC.               JC22 @G@@[]          J VJ
)@@G@@        LINKRR.   JOIN RETURN CODE IN LINK ROUTINE.    JC22 @G@@[]. ****VK
)@@G@@*****************************************************RTNR****JC22 @G@@[]VL
)@@G@@. *********************************************************RTNS****JC22 VM
)@@G@@@G@@[].         CALL  RTNS(S(I))                                        VN
)@@G@@ JC22 @G@@[].                                                           VO
)@@G@@       JC22 @G@@[]. THIS FORTRAN STATEMENT IS USED TO RETURN A STRING FRVP
)@@G@@OM AN        JC22 @G@@[]. EXTERNAL FUNCTION.  S() IS AN ARRAY THAT CONTAVQ
)@@G@@INS THE STRING     JC22 @G@@[]. IN THE FOLLOWING FORM:  S(I) IS THE LENGVR
)@@G@@TH OF THE STRING IN      JC22 @G@@[]. CHARACTERS; THE STRING IS PACKED 6VS
)@@G@@ CHARACTERS PER WORD INTO      JC22 @G@@[]. S(I+1), S(I+2), ETC.  AS A SVT
)@@G@@PECIAL CASE,                         JC22 @G@@[].         CALL  RTNS(0) VU
)@@G@@                                           JC22 @G@@[]. RETURNS THE NULLVV
)@@G@@ STRING.  NOTE THAT, LIKE THE OTHER SPECIAL      JC22 @G@@[]. RETURN FUNVW
)@@G@@CTIONS, RTNS WILL CAUSE AN IMMEDIATE RETURN EVEN IF    JC22 @G@@[]. IT IVX
)@@G@@S CALLED FROM WITHIN A SET OF NESTED FUNCTION CALLS.         JC22 @G@@[]VY
)@@G@@.                                                                  JC22 VZ
)@@G@@@G@@[]$(2).                                                             WA
)@@G@@ JC22 @G@@[]SRTNSP    SPEC      *0,*0,*0,*0,*0. LOCAL SPECIFIER FOR STRIWB
)@@G@@NG     JC22 @G@@[]SRTND1    DESCR     SRTNSP,*0,S.   DESCRIPTOR FOR THISWC
)@@G@@ STRING.     JC22 @G@@[]SRTND2    DESCR     *0,*0,*0.      SCRATCH DESCRWD
)@@G@@IPTOR.             JC22 @G@@[].                                         WE
)@@G@@                         JC22 @G@@[]$(1).                               WF
)@@G@@                               JC22 @G@@[]RTNS**.                       WG
)@@G@@                                     JC22 @G@@[]          LA,U      A3,3WH
)@@G@@.     SET RETURN-TYPE INDICATOR.           JC22 @G@@[]          LA      WI
)@@G@@  A0,0,X11. GET ADDR OF S(I).                    JC22 @G@@[]          LAWJ
)@@G@@        A2,0,A0.       GET S(I).                       JC22 @G@@[]      WK
)@@G@@    JNZ       A2,SRTN1.      IS IT ZERO?                     JC22 @G@@[]WL
)@@G@@          DL        A0,NULVCL.  YES--GET NULL STRING DESCRIPTOR.   JC22 WM
)@@G@@@G@@[]          J         SRTNIT.   GO RETURN IT.                       WN
)@@G@@ JC22 @G@@[].                                                           WO
)@@G@@       JC22 @G@@[].                             BUILD SPECIFIER TO STRINWP
)@@G@@G:           JC22 @G@@[]SRTN1     SA        A0,SRTNSP.     PUT ADDR OF SWQ
)@@G@@(I) IN A-FIELD.    JC22 @G@@[]          LA,U      A1,1.          OFFSET WR
)@@G@@= 1 WORD.                JC22 @G@@[]          SA        A1,SRTNSP+2.   PWS
)@@G@@UT IN /-FIELD.                 JC22 @G@@[]          SA        A2,SRTNSP+WT
)@@G@@3.   PUT SIZE IN L-FIELD.            JC22 @G@@[]          RCALL     SRTNWU
)@@G@@D2,GENVAR SRTND1 *0.                       JC22 @G@@[].                 WV
)@@G@@                 GENERATE SNOBOL4 STRING.        JC22 @G@@[]          DLWW
)@@G@@        A0,SRTND2.     LOAD DESCRIPTOR TO RETURN.      JC22 @G@@[]SRTNITWX
)@@G@@    LX        X8,LINKX8.     GET LOC TO PUT VALUE.           JC22 @G@@[]WY
)@@G@@          DS        A0,0,X8.       STORE RETURN VALUE.             JC22 WZ
)@@G@@@G@@[]          J         LINKRR.        JOIN LINKS RETURN CODE.        XA
)@@G@@ JC22 @G@@[]. *********************************************************RXB
)@@G@@TNS****JC22 @G@@[]          LOFF.                                       XC
)@@G@@             JC10 @I@@@@. **********************************************XD
)@@G@@***********SPCIN$**JC30             @I@@@@SPCIN$*.                      XE
)@@G@@         CONVERT SPECIFIER TO INTEGER                 @I@@@@FAIL      EQXF
)@@G@@UF      0,X11.                                                          XG
)@@G@@@I@@@@SPEC      EQUF      0,A0.                                         XH
)@@G@@                  @I@@@@          LA        A6,SPEC+3.                  XI
)@@G@@                                    @I@@@@          JZ        A6,OUT.   XJ
)@@G@@                                                      @I@@@@          LAXK
)@@G@@,H2     A2,SPEC+2.                                                      XL
)@@G@@@I@@@@          LA,H1     A3,SPEC+2.                                    XM
)@@G@@                  @I@@@@          AA        A2,SPEC.                    XN
)@@G@@                                    @I@@@@          LXI,U     A2,1.     XO
)@@G@@                                                      @I@@@@          LXXP
)@@G@@I,U     A3,1.                                                           XQ
)@@G@@@I@@@@          LR        R1,SPEC+3.                                    XR
)@@G@@                  @I@@@@          LA,XU     A0,-1.                      XS
)@@G@@                                    @I@@@@          LA,U      A1,9.     XT
)@@G@@                                                      @I@@@@          DSXU
)@@G@@L       A5,72.                                                          XV
)@@G@@@I@@@@          JGD       R1,$+2.                                       XW
)@@G@@                  @I@@@@          J         FAIL.                       XX
)@@G@@                                    @I@@@@          EX        CHRLA4,*A3XY
)@@G@@.                                                     @I@@@@          TNXZ
)@@G@@E,U     A4,'+'.                                                         YA
)@@G@@@I@@@@          J         $+4.                                          YB
)@@G@@                  @I@@@@          TE,U      A4,'-'.                     YC
)@@G@@                                    @I@@@@          J         NEXT+1.   YD
)@@G@@                                                      @I@@@@          LAYE
)@@G@@,U      A5,1.                                                           YF
)@@G@@@I@@@@          JGD       R1,$+2.                                       YG
)@@G@@                  @I@@@@          J         FAIL.                       YH
)@@G@@                                    @I@@@@NEXT      EX        CHRLA4,*A3YI
)@@G@@.                                                     @I@@@@          ANYJ
)@@G@@A,U     A4,'0'.                                                         YK
)@@G@@@I@@@@          TW        A0,A4.                                        YL
)@@G@@                  @I@@@@          J         FAIL.                       YM
)@@G@@                                    @I@@@@          MF,U      A6,10.    YN
)@@G@@                                                      @I@@@@          JNYO
)@@G@@Z       A6,FAIL.                                                        YP
)@@G@@@I@@@@          DSC       A6,37.                                        YQ
)@@G@@                  @I@@@@          AA        A6,A4.                      YR
)@@G@@                                    @I@@@@          JO        FAIL.     YS
)@@G@@                                                      @I@@@@          JGYT
)@@G@@D       R1,NEXT.                                                        YU
)@@G@@@I@@@@          JZ        A5,$+2.                                       YV
)@@G@@                  @I@@@@          LNA       A6,A6.                      YW
)@@G@@                                    @I@@@@OUT       LA,U      A7,INTDT. YX
)@@G@@                                                      @I@@@@          J YY
)@@G@@        1,X11.                                                          YZ
)@@G@@@I@@@@. *********************************************************SPCIN$*ZA
)@@G@@*JC30             @I@@@@. **********************************************ZB
)@@G@@***********STPRNTS*JC11             @I@@@@. STPRNTS IS THE SUBROUTINE FOZC
)@@G@@R STPRNT.  IT IS CALLED AS:          JC11             @I@@@@.         LAZD
)@@G@@,U      A2,STPRNT(1,2).     D2--D1 NOT USED YET.       JC11             ZE
)@@G@@@I@@@@.         LA,U      A3,STPRNT(1,3).     SP = STRING TO PRINT.     ZF
)@@G@@ JC11             @I@@@@.         LMJ       X10,STPRNTS.        NOTE X10ZG
)@@G@@!                  JC11             @I@@@@.                             ZH
)@@G@@                                     JC11             @I@@@@.  THE ACTUAZI
)@@G@@L OUTPUT IS HANDLED BY THE FOLLOWING CALLS ON FORTRAN  JC11             ZJ
)@@G@@@I@@@@.  OUTPUT AND FORMATTING ROUTINES:                                ZK
)@@G@@ JC11             @I@@@@.         LMJ       X11,NWDU$.                  ZL
)@@G@@                   JC11             @I@@@@.         +         1,U.      ZM
)@@G@@                                     JC11             @I@@@@.         + ZN
)@@G@@        F.                                             JC11             ZO
)@@G@@@I@@@@.         +         W.                                            ZP
)@@G@@ JC11             @I@@@@.  THIS DOES INITIALIZATION OF THE OUTPUT OPERATZQ
)@@G@@ION, WHERE         JC11             @I@@@@.     U = ADDRESS OF THE WORD ZR
)@@G@@CONTAINING THE UNIT NUMBER.          JC11             @I@@@@.     F = ADZS
)@@G@@DRESS OF THE FORMAT.                                   JC11             ZT
)@@G@@@I@@@@.     W = WALKBACK INFO--NOT NEEDED.                              ZU
)@@G@@ JC11             @I@@@@.  THE ITEMS TO BE OUTPUT ARE THEN FED ONE AT A ZV
)@@G@@TIME TO THE FORMATTJC11             @I@@@@.  ROUTINE BY DOING THE FOLLOWZW
)@@G@@ING FOR EACH ITEM:                   JC11             @I@@@@.         CAZX
)@@G@@LCULATE ITEM TO OUTPUT.                                JC11             ZY
)@@G@@@I@@@@.         LA,U      A0,A.                                         ZZ
)@@G@@ JC11             @I@@@@.         SLJ       NIO1$.                      AA
)@@G@@                   JC11             @I@@@@.  WHERE A IS THE ADDRESS CONTAB
)@@G@@AINING THE ITEM.  NOTE THAT A MUST NOJC11             @I@@@@.  BE A CONTAC
)@@G@@ROL REGISTER, BECAUSE NIO1$ MAY DO A PARTIAL WORD OPERAJC11             AD
)@@G@@@I@@@@.  ON THE ITEM, AND SUCH OPERATIONS DON'T WORK FOR REGISTERS.  ALSAE
)@@G@@OJC11             @I@@@@.  NIO1$ (AND NWDU$ TOO) WILL DESTROY A0, SO IT AF
)@@G@@MUST BE LOADED ANEWJC11             @I@@@@.  EACH ITEM, EVEN IF IT IS THAG
)@@G@@E SAME FOR ALL OF THEM.              JC11             @I@@@@.     WHEN AAH
)@@G@@LL ITEMS HAVE BEEN FED TO NIO1$, THE OUTPUT OPERATION MJC11             AI
)@@G@@@I@@@@.  BE FINISHED UP BY A CALL OF:                                   AJ
)@@G@@ JC11             @I@@@@.         SLJ       NIO2$.                      AK
)@@G@@                   JC11             @I@@@@.                             AL
)@@G@@                                     JC11             @I@]@@$(0).       AM
)@@G@@                                                       JC11             AN
)@@G@@@G@@[]$(2).                                                             AO
)@@G@@ JC11 @I[@@@ONECHAR   +         0.             CHARACTER BUFFER FOR NIO1AP
)@@G@@$.     JC11             @I@@@@$(1).                                     AQ
)@@G@@                         JC11             @I@@@@STPRNTS**.              AR
)@@G@@           STPRNT SUBROUTINE.              JC11             @I@@@@      AS
)@@G@@    LA        A0,0,A2.       A(D2).                          JC11       AT
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          LA        A14,2,A0.      A(A(D2)+D) = UNIT NUMBER.AU
)@@G@@       JC11             @I@@@@          LA        A0,4,A0.       A(A(D2)AV
)@@G@@+2D) = FORMAT BLOCK ADDR.JC11             @I@@@@          AA,U      A0,8AW
)@@G@@.          + 4D = 1ST WORD OF FORMAT.      JC11             @I@@@@      AX
)@@G@@    SA        A0,FST.        PUT IN NDWU$ CALLING SEQUENCE.  JC11       AY
)@@G@@      @I@@@@.                                                           AZ
)@@G@@       JC11             @I@@@@          LX        X2,0,A3.       A(SP). BA
)@@G@@                         JC11             @I@@@@          AX,H2     X2,2BB
)@@G@@,A3.       A(SP)+OW(SP) = STARTING WORD.   JC11             @I@@@@      BC
)@@G@@    LX,H1     X3,2,A3.       OC(SP) = CHAR WITHIN WORD.      JC11       BD
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          LA        A6,3,A3.       L(SP) = NUMBER OF CHARS TBE
)@@G@@O PRINTJC11             @I@@@@          LXI,U     X2,1.                 BF
)@@G@@                         JC11             @I@@@@          LXI,U     X3,1BG
)@@G@@.                                          JC11             @I@@@@.     BH
)@@G@@                                                             JC11       BI
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          LMJ       X11,NWDU$.     CALL FORTRAN OUTPUT ROUTIBJ
)@@G@@NE--INIJC11             @I@@@@          +         1,A14.         ?, UNITBK
)@@G@@ NUMBER.                 JC11             @I@@@@FST       +         0.  BL
)@@G@@           FORMAT ADDRESS.                 JC11             @I@@@@      BM
)@@G@@    +         0,0.           WALKBACK INFO.                  JC11       BN
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          J         STPRTEST.      GET LIST OF CHARS TO PRINBO
)@@G@@T.     JC11             @I@@@@STPRNEXT  EX        CHRLA5,*X3.    GET A CBP
)@@G@@HAR FROM STRING.         JC11             @I@@@@          SA,S1     A5,OBQ
)@@G@@NECHAR.    PUT IT INTO BUFFER              JC11             @I@@@@      BR
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,ONECHAR.    A0 MUST CONTAIN ADDRESS OF ARG. JC11       BS
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          SLJ       NIO1$.         PROCESS IT, PUT IN BUFFERBT
)@@G@@.      JC11             @I@@@@STPRTEST  JGD       A6,STPRNEXT.   ANY CHABU
)@@G@@RS LEFT?                 JC11             @I@@@@          SLJ       NIO2BV
)@@G@@$.         IF NOT, WRAP IT ALL UP.         JC11             @I@@@@      BW
)@@G@@    J         0,X10.         AND RETURN.                     JC11       BX
)@@G@@      @I@@@@. *********************************************************SBY
)@@G@@TPRNTS*JC11             @I@@@@. ****************************************BZ
)@@G@@*****************STREAMS*JC30             @I@@@@. THIS IS THE STREAM SUBCA
)@@G@@ROUTINE.  A CALL OF:                       JC30             @I@@@@.     CB
)@@G@@                                                             JC30       CC
)@@G@@      @I@@@@.         STREAM    S1,S2,T,ERR,RUNOUT,SUCC.                CD
)@@G@@       JC30             @I@@@@.                                         CE
)@@G@@                         JC30             @I@@@@. IS EXPANDED TO:       CF
)@@G@@                                           JC30             @I@@@@.     CG
)@@G@@                                                             JC30       CH
)@@G@@      @I@@@@.         LX,U      X2,S1.                                  CI
)@@G@@       JC30             @I@@@@.         LX,U      X3,S2.                CJ
)@@G@@                         JC30             @I@@@@.         LX,U      A2,TCK
)@@G@@.                                          JC30             @I@@@@.     CL
)@@G@@    LX,U      X9,ERR.                                        JC30       CM
)@@G@@      @I@@@@.         LX,U      X10,RUNOUT.                             CN
)@@G@@       JC30             @I@@@@.         LX,U      X11,SUCC.             CO
)@@G@@                         JC30             @I@@@@.         J         STRECP
)@@G@@AMS.                                       JC30             @I@@@@.     CQ
)@@G@@                                                             JC30       CR
)@@G@@      @I@@@@. THE FORMAT OF A SYNTAX TABLE ENTRY IS:                    CS
)@@G@@       JC30             @I@@@@.         H1 = ACTION TO TAKE FOR CHAR:   CT
)@@G@@                         JC30             @I@@@@.              >0: GOTO/CU
)@@G@@CONTIN; TABLES+H1 = NEXT TABLE TO USE.     JC30             @I@@@@.     CV
)@@G@@         -1: ERROR                                           JC30       CW
)@@G@@      @I@@@@.              -2: STOP                                     CX
)@@G@@       JC30             @I@@@@.              -3: STOPSH                 CY
)@@G@@                         JC30             @I@@@@.         H2 = PUT (OR ZCZ
)@@G@@ERO IF NOTHING SPECIFIED).                 JC30             @I@@@@.     DA
)@@G@@                                                             JC30       DB
)@@G@@      @I@@@@CHADD.                        CHARACTER ADD ROUTINE:        DC
)@@G@@       JC30             @I@@@@          AA,S1     A2,0,A0.  CALL AS:    DD
)@@G@@                         JC30             @I@@@@          AA,S2     A2,0DE
)@@G@@,A0.       EX   CHADD,*A1.                 JC30             @I@@@@      DF
)@@G@@    AA,S3     A2,0,A0.  WHERE:                               JC30       DG
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          AA,S4     A2,0,A0.       A0 = WORD CONTAINING CHARDH
)@@G@@.      JC30             @I@@@@          AA,S5     A2,0,A0.       A1 = CHDI
)@@G@@AR WITHIN WORD (0-5).    JC30             @I@@@@          LMJ       X1,$DJ
)@@G@@+1.        A2 = ADDRESS CHAR IS TO BE ADDEDJC30             @I@@@@      DK
)@@G@@    AA,S6     A2,0,*A0.                                      JC30       DL
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          LXM,U     A1,0.                                   DM
)@@G@@       JC30             @I@@@@          J         0,X1.                 DN
)@@G@@                         JC30             @I@@@@.                       DO
)@@G@@                                           JC30             @I@@@@STREAMDP
)@@G@@S**.                    ENTRY POINT TO STREAM SUBROUTINE.    JC30       DQ
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          LA        A0,0,X3.       A(S2)                    DR
)@@G@@       JC30             @I@@@@          AA,H2     A0,2,X3.       + OW(S2DS
)@@G@@)                        JC30             @I@@@@          LA,H1     A1,2DT
)@@G@@,X3.       OC(S2)                          JC30             @I@@@@      DU
)@@G@@    LA        A10,3,X3.      L(S2)                           JC30       DV
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          SZ        A5.            A5 = 'PUT' ITEM.         DW
)@@G@@       JC30             @I@@@@          LXI,U     A0,1.          INCREMEDX
)@@G@@NTS = 1                  JC30             @I@@@@          LXI,U     A1,1DY
)@@G@@.          '                               JC30             @I@@@@      DZ
)@@G@@    J         STRYY.         GOT ANY CHARS AT ALL?           JC30       EA
)@@G@@      @I@@@@.                                                           EB
)@@G@@       JC30             @I@@@@STRXX.                             LOOK ATEC
)@@G@@ TABLE ENTRY FOR NEXT CHAJC30             @I@@@@          JZ        A2,GED
)@@G@@OTOZERO.   ERROR IF TABLE ADDRESS ZERO.    JC30             @I@@@@      EE
)@@G@@    EX        CHADD,*A1.     SET A2 TO LOC OF TABLE ENTRY.   JC30       EF
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          LA        A13,A2.        IN CASE OF DUMP.         EG
)@@G@@       JC30             @I@@@@          TZ,H2     0,A2.          PUT ITEEH
)@@G@@M PRESENT?               JC30             @I@@@@          LA,H2     A5,0EI
)@@G@@,A2.       YES--SAVE IT IN A5.             JC30             @I@@@@      EJ
)@@G@@    LA,XH1    A2,0,A2.       WHAT TO DO WITH THIS CHAR?      JC30       EK
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          JP        A2,STRGOTO.    IF > 0, GO ON TO NEXT CHAEL
)@@G@@R.     JC30             @I@@@@          LMA       A2,A2.         < 0--GEEM
)@@G@@T MAGNITUDE, WHICH IS TAGJC30             @I@@@@          TG,U      A2,4EN
)@@G@@.          IS IT A VALID TAG?              JC30             @I@@@@      EO
)@@G@@    J         BADTAG.        NO (>3).                        JC30       EP
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          J         $+1,A2.        VALID TAG--JUMP TABLE:   EQ
)@@G@@       JC30             @I@@@@          J         BADTAG.        -0--NOTER
)@@G@@ A VALID TAG YET.        JC30             @I@@@@          J         STREES
)@@G@@RR.        ERROR TAG.                      JC30             @I@@@@      ET
)@@G@@    J         STRSTOP.       STOP TAG.                       JC30       EU
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          J         STRSTOPSH.     STOPSH TAG.              EV
)@@G@@       JC30             @I@@@@.                                  CONTIN EW
)@@G@@OR GOTO TAG:             JC30             @I@@@@STRGOTO.                EX
)@@G@@           APPLY TABLE TO NEXT CHAR:       JC30             @I@@@@      EY
)@@G@@    AA,U      A2,TABLES.     GET ADDRESS OF NEXT TABLE.      JC30       EZ
)@@G@@      @I@@@@STRYY     JGD       A10,STRXX.     ANY MORE CHARS IN STRING?FA
)@@G@@       JC30             @I@@@@.                                  RUNOUT FB
)@@G@@TERMINATION:             JC30             @I@@@@          SA        A5,SFC
)@@G@@TYPE.      RUNOUT CODE--SET STYPE.         JC30             @I@@@@      FD
)@@G@@    DL        A5,0,X3.       COPY S2 TO S1.                  JC30       FE
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          DS        A5,0,X2.       A-F-V                    FF
)@@G@@       JC30             @I@@@@          DL        A5,2,X3.              FG
)@@G@@                         JC30             @I@@@@          DS        A5,2FH
)@@G@@,X2.       O-L                             JC30             @I@@@@      FI
)@@G@@    SZ        3,X3.          SET L(S2) TO ZERO.              JC30       FJ
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          J         0,X10.         RUNOUT EXIT.             FK
)@@G@@       JC30             @I@@@@.                                         FL
)@@G@@                         JC30             @I@@@@STRERR.                 FM
)@@G@@           TAG = 'ERROR'                   JC30             @I@@@@      FN
)@@G@@    SZ        STYPE.         STYPE = 0.                      JC30       FO
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          DL        A5,0,X3.       COPY S2 TO S1            FP
)@@G@@       JC30             @I@@@@          DS        A5,0,X2.       A-F-V  FQ
)@@G@@                         JC30             @I@@@@          DL        A5,2FR
)@@G@@,X3.                                       JC30             @I@@@@      FS
)@@G@@    DS        A5,2,X2.       O-L                             JC30       FT
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          J         0,X9.          ERROR EXIT.              FU
)@@G@@       JC30             @I@@@@.                                         FV
)@@G@@                         JC30             @I@@@@STRSTOP.                FW
)@@G@@           TAG = 'STOP'                    JC30             @I@@@@      FX
)@@G@@    SA        A5,STYPE.      STYPE = 'PUT' ITEM.             JC30       FY
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          DL        A4,0,X3.       COPY AFV(S2)             FZ
)@@G@@       JC30             @I@@@@          DS        A4,0,X2.              GA
)@@G@@                         JC30             @I@@@@          DL        A4,2GB
)@@G@@,X3.       A4,5 = OL(S2)                   JC30             @I@@@@      GC
)@@G@@    SA        A4,2,X2.       PUT O(S2) IN O(S1).             JC30       GD
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          ANU       A5,A10.        GET J = L(S2) - # CHARS LGE
)@@G@@EFT.   JC30             @I@@@@          SA        A6,3,X2.       L(S1) =GF
)@@G@@ J                       JC30             @I@@@@          ANA       A0,0GG
)@@G@@,X3.       GET BACK OFFSET (WORD PART).    JC30             @I@@@@      GH
)@@G@@    SA,H2     A0,2,X3.       OW(S2) = A0                     JC30       GI
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          SA,H1     A1,2,X3.       OC(S2) = A1.             GJ
)@@G@@       JC30             @I@@@@          SA        A10,3,X3.      L(S2) =GK
)@@G@@ A10 = # CHARS LEFT      JC30             @I@@@@          J         0,X1GL
)@@G@@1.         SUCCESS EXIT.                   JC30             @I@@@@.     GM
)@@G@@                                                             JC30       GN
)@@G@@      @I@@@@STRSTOPSH.                         TAG = 'STOPSH'--BACK UP AGO
)@@G@@ CHAR. JC30             @I@@@@          LXI,U     A1,0.          SO TESTGP
)@@G@@ WILL WORK PROPERLY:     JC30             @I@@@@          AA,U      A10,GQ
)@@G@@1.         ADD 1 TO # CHARS LEFT.          JC30             @I@@@@      GR
)@@G@@    JNZ       A1,$+3.        SUBTRACT 1 FROM A0,1:           JC30       GS
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          ANA,U     A0,1.                                   GT
)@@G@@       JC30             @I@@@@          LA,U      A1,6.                 GU
)@@G@@                         JC30             @I@@@@          ANA,U     A1,1GV
)@@G@@.                                          JC30             @I@@@@      GW
)@@G@@    J         STRSTOP.       REST SAME AS 'STOP'.            JC30       GX
)@@G@@      @I@@@@.                                                           GY
)@@G@@       JC30             @I@@@@.                                         GZ
)@@G@@                         JC10             @I@@@@BADTAG    X$MESG    3.  HA
)@@G@@           TAG NOT IN RANGE 1-4.           JC10             @I@@@@      HB
)@@G@@    'BAD TAG (IN A2).'.                                      JC10       HC
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          ER        ERR$.                                   HD
)@@G@@       JC10             @I@@@@.                                         HE
)@@G@@                         JC10             @I@@@@GOTOZERO  X$MESG    3.  HF
)@@G@@           GOTO TAG WITH ZERO ADDRESS      JC10             @I@@@@      HG
)@@G@@    'GOTO(0)--SEE A13.'.                                     JC10       HH
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          ER        ERR$.                                   HI
)@@G@@       JC10             @I@@@@.                                         HJ
)@@G@@                         JC10             @I@@@@. **********************HK
)@@G@@***********************************STREAMS*JC30             @I@@@@. ****HL
)@@G@@*****************************************************STRLS***JC04       HM
)@@G@@      @I@@@@. THIS IS THE STRING-REAL CONVERSION SUBROUTINE.  IT IS INVOHN
)@@G@@KED BY JC04             @I@@@@. A CALL OF:                              HO
)@@G@@                         JC04             @I@@@@.         SPREAL    DESCHP
)@@G@@R,SPEC,FAILURE,SUCCESS.                    JC04             @I@@@@. WHICHQ
)@@G@@H IS EXPANDED TO:                                            JC04       HR
)@@G@@      @I@@@@.         LX,U      X8,DESCR.                               HS
)@@G@@       JC04             @I@@@@.         LX,U      X9,SPEC.              HT
)@@G@@                         JC04             @I@@@@.         LX,U      X10,HU
)@@G@@FAILURE.                                   JC04             @I@@@@.     HV
)@@G@@    LX,U      X11,SUCCESS.                                   JC04       HW
)@@G@@      @I@@@@.         J         STRLS.                                  HX
)@@G@@       JC04             @I@@@@. IF FAILURE OR SUCCESS EXITS ARE MISSING,HY
)@@G@@ THEY ARE DEFINED (SEE   JC04             @I@@@@. SPREAL) AS THE LOCATIOHZ
)@@G@@N AFTER THE 'J  STRLS.' INSTRUCTION.       JC04             @I@@@@. SPECIA
)@@G@@ POINTS TO A STRING TO BE CONVERTED TO A REAL NUMBER.  A(DESCJC04       IB
)@@G@@      @I@@@@. IS ASSIGNED THE NUMBER; F(DESCR) IS SET TO 0; V(DESCR) IS IC
)@@G@@SET    JC04             @I@@@@. TO REALDT, THE TYPE-CODE FOR REALS.  IF ID
)@@G@@THE STRING ISN'T A VALID JC04             @I@@@@. REAL NUMBER, TRANSFER IE
)@@G@@IS TO FAILURE AND DESCR IS UNALTERED.      JC04             @I@@@@. IF SIF
)@@G@@UCCESSFUL, TRANSFER IS TO SUCCESS.                           JC04       IG
)@@G@@      @I@@@@.                                                           IH
)@@G@@       JC04             @I@@@@. THERE SHOULDN'T BE ANY TROUBLE OVER 64K.II
)@@G@@                         JC04             @I@@@@.                       IJ
)@@G@@                                           JC04             @I@@@@. X1-XIK
)@@G@@4, X7-X15, A0-A3, A5-A6, A8-A11, A13 ARE ALL USED, AND THERE JC04       IL
)@@G@@      @I@@@@. MAY BE OTHERS THAT I DON'T KNOW ABOUT.                    IM
)@@G@@       JC04             @I@@@@.                                         IN
)@@G@@                         JC04             @I@@@@.                       IO
)@@G@@                                           JC04             @I@]@@      IP
)@@G@@    LON.                                                     JC04       IQ
)@@G@@      @I[@@@.                                                           IR
)@@G@@       JC04             @I@@@@.         CHARACTER LOAD ROUTINE:         IS
)@@G@@                         JC04             @I@@@@STRLLD.                 IT
)@@G@@                                           JC04             @I@@@@      IU
)@@G@@    LA,S1     A3,0,A0.                                       JC04       IV
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          LA,S2     A3,0,A0.                                IW
)@@G@@       JC04             @I@@@@          LA,S3     A3,0,A0.              IX
)@@G@@                         JC04             @I@@@@          LA,S4     A3,0IY
)@@G@@,A0.                                       JC04             @I@@@@      IZ
)@@G@@    LA,S5     A3,0,A0.                                       JC04       JA
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          LA,S6     A3,0,A0.                                JB
)@@G@@       JC04             @I@@@@          J         RTST+2.   7TH CHAR?  GJC
)@@G@@ET NEXT WORD.            JC04             @I@@@@.                       JD
)@@G@@                                           JC04             @I@@@@.     JE
)@@G@@    CONVERSION ROUTINE:                                      JC04       JF
)@@G@@      @I@@@@STRLS*.                                                     JG
)@@G@@       JC04             @I@@@@          LA,U      A5,057.   '0', LOWER BJH
)@@G@@OUND FOR TNW TEST.       JC04             @I@@@@          LA,U      A6,0JI
)@@G@@71.   '9'+1, UPPER BOUND                   JC04             @I@@@@      JJ
)@@G@@    SZ        X4.                                            JC04       JK
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          SZ        X7.                                     JL
)@@G@@       JC04             @I@@@@          SZ        A8.                   JM
)@@G@@                         JC04             @I@@@@          LA        A13,JN
)@@G@@(+1.0).    FINAL SIGN                      JC04             @I@@@@      JO
)@@G@@    LA,U      A10,155.       EXPONENT BIAS                   JC04       JP
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          LA        A0,0,X9.       ADDR OF 1ST CHAR. OF STRIJQ
)@@G@@NG     JC04             @I@@@@          AA,H2     A0,2,X9.              JR
)@@G@@                         JC04             @I@@@@          LXI,U     A0,1JS
)@@G@@.                                          JC04             @I@@@@      JT
)@@G@@    LX,H1     X1,2,X9.       CHAR WITHIN WORD.               JC04       JU
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          LXI,U     X1,1.                                   JV
)@@G@@       JC04             @I@@@@          LX,U      X2,6.          # CHARSJW
)@@G@@/WORD                    JC04             @I@@@@          LX        X3,3JX
)@@G@@,X9.       SIZE OF STRING                  JC04             @I@@@@.     JY
)@@G@@                                                             JC04       JZ
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          ANX,U     X3,1.          GET FIRST CHAR:          KA
)@@G@@       JC04             @I@@@@          EX        STRLLD,*X1.           KB
)@@G@@                         JC04             @I@@@@          TE,U      A3,'KC
)@@G@@-'.        NEGATIVE?                       JC04             @I@@@@      KD
)@@G@@    J         LOOP+1.        NO--GO GET NUMBER               JC04       KE
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          LA        A13,(-1.0).    YES--SET FINAL SIGN TO NEKF
)@@G@@G.     JC04             @I@@@@          J         TESTR.         GET NUMKG
)@@G@@BER.                     JC04             @I@@@@.                       KH
)@@G@@                                           JC04             @I@@@@LOOP. KI
)@@G@@                                                             JC04       KJ
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          EX        STRLLD,*X1.    GET A CHAR FROM STRING.  KK
)@@G@@       JC04             @I@@@@          TNW       A5,A3.         IS IT AKL
)@@G@@ DIGIT?                  JC04             @I@@@@          J         ARNDKM
)@@G@@.          IF IT IS, PROCESS IT.           JC04             @I@@@@      KN
)@@G@@    TE,U      A3,'.'.        IF NOT, IS IT A PERIOD?         JC04       KO
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          J         0,X10.         IF NOT, FAIL DUE TO NON-NKP
)@@G@@UMERIC JC04             @I@@@@          LA        A2,X4.         SEE IF KQ
)@@G@@HAVE ALREADY MET A '.'   JC04             @I@@@@          JNZ       A2,0KR
)@@G@@,X10.      IF X4 NONZERO, THIS IS 2ND '.'! JC04             @I@@@@      KS
)@@G@@    LX,U      X7,1.          X7 = 1 MEANS '.' FOUND.         JC04       KT
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          J         TESTR.         GET REST OF NUMBER.      KU
)@@G@@       JC04             @I@@@@.                                         KV
)@@G@@                         JC04             @I@@@@ARND.                   KW
)@@G@@           FOUND A DIGIT:                  JC04             @I@@@@      KX
)@@G@@    ANA,U     A3,060.        FIND NUMERIC VALUE OF DIGIT.    JC04       KY
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          LCF       A10,A3.        CONVERT TO FLOATING (IN AKZ
)@@G@@11).   JC04             @I@@@@          AX        X4,X7.         X4 = # LA
)@@G@@OF DIGITS AFTER '.'.     JC04             @I@@@@          FM        A8,(LB
)@@G@@+10.0).    MULT PREVIOUS VALUE BY 10.      JC04             @I@@@@      LC
)@@G@@    FA        A8,A11.        ADD NEW DIGIT.                  JC04       LD
)@@G@@      @I@@@@TESTR.                             GET NEXT DIGIT:          LE
)@@G@@       JC04             @I@@@@          JGD       X3,RTST.       DECREMELF
)@@G@@NT LENGTH COUNTER.       JC04             @I@@@@          J         SIGNLG
)@@G@@.          IF NOTHING LEFT.                JC04             @I@@@@.     LH
)@@G@@                                                             JC04       LI
)@@G@@      @I@@@@RTST.                                                       LJ
)@@G@@       JC04             @I@@@@          TLEM      X1,X2.         IF H2(SLK
)@@G@@1) NE X2 THEN            JC04             @I@@@@          JGD       X1,LLL
)@@G@@OOP.          IF (X1:=X1-1) >= 0 THEN GOTO JC04             @I@@@@      LM
)@@G@@    LXM,U     X1,0.                                          JC04       LN
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          JMGI      A0,LOOP.       THIS I DON'T UNDERSTAND. LO
)@@G@@       JC04             @I@@@@.                                         LP
)@@G@@                         JC04             @I@@@@SIGN.                   LQ
)@@G@@           FINAL WRAP-UP:                  JC04             @I@@@@      LR
)@@G@@    FM        A8,A13.        SET SIGN.                       JC04       LS
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          FD        A8,P10,X4.     ADJUST FOR # DIGITS AFTERLT
)@@G@@ '.'.  JC04             @I@@@@          SA        A8,0,X8.       PUT NUMLU
)@@G@@BER IN A(DESCR).         JC04             @I@@@@          LA,U      A0,RLV
)@@G@@EALDT.                                     JC04             @I@@@@      LW
)@@G@@    SA        A0,1,X8.       SET TYPE TO REAL.               JC04       LX
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          J         0,X11.         SUCCESSFUL RETURN.       LY
)@@G@@       JC04             @I@]@@          LOFF.                           LZ
)@@G@@                         JC04             @I[@@@. **********************MA
)@@G@@***********************************STRLS***JC04             @I@@@@      MB
)@@G@@    END.      COPYMLINK.                                     JC30       MC
)@@G@@      @I@@@@. *********************************************************CMD

)@@G@@                                                             JC30       MH

)@@G@@*****************************************CPYPAT**JC00             @I@@@@QU
)@@G@@. CPYPAT D1,D2,D3,D4,D5,D6.   'COPY PATTERN'                       JC00 QV
)@@G@@            @I@@@@. COPIES A PATTERN--SEE THE MACRO DOC. FOR DETAILS.  IQW
)@@G@@T'S COMPLEX. JC00             @I@@@@.                                   QX
)@@G@@                               JC00             @I@@@@. SHOULD WORK FOR QY
)@@G@@> 64K.                                           JC00             @I@@@@QZ
)@@G@@.                                                                       RA
)@@G@@            @I@@@@CPYPAT**  PROC      1.                 COPY PATTERN   RB
)@@G@@                              @I@@@@DESCR4    EQU       CPYPAT(1,4).    RC
)@@G@@                                                @I@@@@          LA15    RD
)@@G@@  1.                                             JC30             @I@@@@RE
)@@G@@          LA        A0,CPYPAT(1,6).                                     RF
)@@G@@            @I@@@@          LA        A1,CPYPAT(1,1).                   RG
)@@G@@                              @I@@@@          LA        A2,CPYPAT(1,2). RH
)@@G@@                                                @I@@@@COPY      DL      RI
)@@G@@  A4,2,A2.                                                        @I@@@@RJ
)@@G@@          DS        A4,2,A1.                                            RK
)@@G@@            @I@@@@          DL        A4,4,A2.                          RL
)@@G@@                              @I@@@@          AA        A4,DESCR4.      RM
)@@G@@                                                @I@@@@          TNE     RN
)@@G@@  A4,DESCR4.                                                      @I@@@@RO
)@@G@@          SZ        A4.                                                 RP
)@@G@@            @I@@@@          AA        A5,DESCR4.                        RQ
)@@G@@                              @I@@@@          TNE       A5,DESCR4.      RR
)@@G@@                                                @I@@@@          LA      RS
)@@G@@  A5,CPYPAT(1,5).                                                 @I@@@@RT
)@@G@@          DS        A4,4,A1.                                            RU
)@@G@@            @I@@@@          DL        A4,6,A2.                          RV
)@@G@@                              @I@@@@          AA        A4,CPYPAT(1,3). RW
)@@G@@                                                @I@@@@          AA      RX
)@@G@@  A5,CPYPAT(1,3).                                                 @I@@@@RY
)@@G@@          DS        A4,6,A1.                                            RZ
)@@G@@            @I@@@@          LA,H2     A3,3,A2.       GET V(2+A(D2)) = V7SA
)@@G@@.            JC30             @I@@@@          TE,U      A3,3.          ISB
)@@G@@F V7=3, COPY R2+4D TO R1+4D.   JC30             @I@@@@          J       SC
)@@G@@  NEXT.          IF NOT, DON'T.                  JC30             @I@@@@SD
)@@G@@          DL        A4,8,A2.                                            SE
)@@G@@            @I@@@@          DS        A4,8,A1.                          SF
)@@G@@                              @I@@@@NEXT      LA,H2     A3,3,A2.        SG
)@@G@@    V(2+A(D2))  [= V7]         JC30             @I@@@@          AA,U    SH
)@@G@@  A3,1.               1 + V7                     JC30             @I@@@@SI
)@@G@@          LSSC      A3,1.                                               SJ
)@@G@@            @I@@@@          ANA       A0,A3.                            SK
)@@G@@                              @I@@@@          AA        A1,A3.          SL
)@@G@@                                                @I@@@@          TLE,U   SM
)@@G@@  A0,1.          IF A0 LT 1, FINISHED.           JC30             @I@@@@SN
)@@G@@          J         DONE.                                          JC30 SO
)@@G@@            @I@@@@          AA        A2,A3.                            SP
)@@G@@                              @I@@@@          J         COPY.           SQ
)@@G@@                                                @I@@@@DONE.             SR
)@@G@@                 FINISHED--STORE RESULT IN A1:   JC30             @I@@@@SS
)@@G@@          SA        A1,CPYPAT(1,1).                                     ST
)@@G@@            @I@@@@          LA15      0.                                SU
)@@G@@             JC30             @I@]@@          LOFF.                     SV
)@@G@@                               JC10             @I[@@@          END.    SW
)@@G@@                                                                  @I@@@@SX
)@@G@@. *********************************************************CPYPAT**JC00 SY
)@@G@@            @I@@@@. ****************************************************SZ
)@@G@@*****DATE****JC00             @I@@@@DATE**    PROC      1.              TA
)@@G@@   GET DATE                                     @I@@@@SPEC      EQU     TB
)@@G@@  DATE(1,1).                                                      @I@@@@TC
)@@G@@          ER        DATE$.                                              TD
)@@G@@            @I@@@@          SA,T1     A0,DATBUF+1.                      TE
)@@G@@                              @I@@@@          SSL       A0,12.          TF
)@@G@@                                                @I@@@@          SA,S5   TG
)@@G@@  A0,DATBUF.                                                      @I@@@@TH
)@@G@@          SSL       A0,6.                                               TI
)@@G@@            @I@@@@          SA,S4     A0,DATBUF.                        TJ
)@@G@@                              @I@@@@          SSL       A0,6.           TK
)@@G@@                                                @I@@@@          SA,T1   TL
)@@G@@  A0,DATBUF.                                                      @I@@@@TM
)@@G@@          LA,U      A0,DATBUF.                                          TN
)@@G@@            @I@@@@          SA        A0,SPEC.                          TO
)@@G@@                              @I@@@@          SZ        SPEC+1.         TP
)@@G@@                                                @I@@@@          SZ      TQ
)@@G@@  SPEC+2.                                                         @I@@@@TR
)@@G@@          LA,U      A0,8.                                               TS
)@@G@@            @I@@@@          SA        A0,SPEC+3.                        TT
)@@G@@                              @I@@@@          END.                      TU

)@@G@@DEQL**    PROC      1.                  DESCRIPTOR EQUAL TEST           UH
)@@G@@            @I@@@@          DL        A0,DEQL(1,1).                     UI
)@@G@@                              @I@@@@          DTE       A0,DEQL(1,2).   UJ
)@@G@@                                                @I@@@@          J       UK
)@@G@@  LOC.                                                            @I@@@@UL
)@@G@@          DO 1-DEQL(1,*4) , J DEQL(1,4).                                UM
)@@G@@            @I@@@@LOC       LOCC      DEQL(1,3),$.   FAIL EXIT HERE IF MUN
)@@G@@ISSING.      JC30             @I@]@@          LOFF.                     UO
)@@G@@                               JC10             @I[@@@          END.    UP
