)@@G@@PREAL**JC00             @I@@@@. SPREAL  DE,SP,F,S.          'CONVERT SPEKO
)@@G@@CIFIED STRING TO REAL'   JC04             @I@@@@.                       KP
)@@G@@                                           JC04             @I@@@@. THISKQ
)@@G@@ IS THE STRING-REAL CONVERSION MACRO.  SP POINTS TO THE      JC04       KR
)@@G@@      @I@@@@. STRING TO BE CONVERTED, AND THE RESULT IS GIVEN TO A(DE). KS
)@@G@@       JC04             @I@@@@. V(DE) IS SET TO 0; F(DE) IS SET TO REALDKT
)@@G@@T.                       JC04             @I@@@@.                       KU
)@@G@@                                           JC04             @I@@@@. THISKV
)@@G@@ SHOULD WORK FOR > 64K.                                      JC04       KW
)@@G@@      @I@@@@.                                                           KX
)@@G@@       JC04             @I@@@@. X1-X4, X7-X15, A0-A3, A5-A6, A8-A11, A13KY
)@@G@@ ARE USED (AND POSSIBLY  JC04             @I@@@@. OTHERS THAT I DON'T KNKZ
)@@G@@OW ABOUT YET).                             JC04             @I@@@@.     LA
)@@G@@                                                             JC04       LB
)@@G@@      @I@@@@SPREAL**  PROC      1.                                      LC
)@@G@@       JC04             @I@@@@          LX,U      X8,SPREAL(1,1).     DELD
)@@G@@.                        JC04             @I@@@@          LX,U      X9,SLE
)@@G@@PREAL(1,2).     SP.                        JC04             @I@@@@      LF
)@@G@@    LX,U      X10,FAIL.           F EXIT.                    JC04       LG
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          LX,U      X11,SUCC.           S EXIT.             LH

)@@G@@NVERSION SUBROUTINE.     JC04             @I@@@@FAIL      LOCC      SPRELJ
)@@G@@AL(1,3),$.      DEFINE EXITS.              JC04             @I@@@@SUCC  LK

)@@G@@*****************************************************SPUSH***JC00       LQ
)@@G@@      @I@@@@SPUSH**   PROC      1.                 PUSH SPECIFIERS ONTO LR
)@@G@@STACK                   @I@@@@          LXI,U     CSTACK,2.             LS
)@@G@@                                          @I@@@@J  DO 2*SPUSH(1) , PUSH2LT
)@@G@@  SPUSH(1,J//2)+(J-1**1)*2.                                 @I@@@@      LU
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,,CSTACK.                                               LV
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          TG,U      A0,STACK+STSIZE.                        LW
)@@G@@                        @I@@@@          J         OVER.                 LX

)@@G@@                                                            @I@@@@. ****LZ

)@@G@@      @I@]@@. *********************************************************SMB
)@@G@@*******JC06             @I@]@@. S,J  R,A,X,H.                    'STORE'MC
)@@G@@                         JC06             @I@]@@.                       MD
)@@G@@                                           JC06             @I@]@@. THISME
)@@G@@ GENERATES A STORE OF THE REGISTER R, DEPENDING ON WHAT SORT JC06       MF
)@@G@@      @I@]@@. REGISTER R IS.  THE RESULT WILL BE ONE OF:                MG
)@@G@@       JC06             @I@]@@.         SX        R,A,X,J+H.     IF R ISMH
)@@G@@ AN X-REGISTER.          JC06             @I@]@@.         SA        R,A,MI
)@@G@@X,J+H.     IF R IS AN A-REGISTER > A3.     JC06             @I@]@@.     MJ
)@@G@@    SR        R,A,X,J+H.     IF R IS AN R-REGISTER.          JC06       MK
)@@G@@      @I@]@@. OTHERWISE NOTHING WILL BE GENERATED.                      ML
)@@G@@       JC06             @I@]@@.                                         MM
)@@G@@                         JC06             @I@]@@STORE**   PROC      1.  MN
)@@G@@                                           JC06             @I@]@@S**   MO
)@@G@@    NAME      0.                                             JC06       MP
)@@G@@      @I@]@@.                                                           MQ
)@@G@@       JC06             @I@]@@J         EQU       STORE(0,2).           MR
)@@G@@                         JC06             @I@]@@R         EQU       STORMS
)@@G@@E(1,1).                                    JC06             @I@]@@A     MT
)@@G@@    EQU       STORE(1,2).                                    JC06       MU
)@@G@@      @I@]@@X         EQU       STORE(1,3).                             MV
)@@G@@       JC06             @I@]@@H         EQU       STORE(1,4).           MW
)@@G@@                         JC06             @I@]@@.                       MX
)@@G@@                                           JC06             @I@]@@ DO R<MY
)@@G@@16 ,           SX       R,A,X,J+H.                           JC06       MZ
)@@G@@      @I@]@@ DO (R>15)**(R<28) , SA       R,A,X,J+H.                    NA
)@@G@@       JC06             @I@]@@ DO (R>63)**(R<79) , SR       R,A,X,J+H.  NB
)@@G@@                         JC06             @I@]@@.                       NC
)@@G@@                                           JC06             @I@]@@      ND
)@@G@@    END.      STORE, S.                                      JC06       NE
)@@G@@      @I@]@@. *********************************************************SNF
)@@G@@*******JC06             @IT@@@. ****************************************NG
)@@G@@*****************STPRNT**JC00             @I@@@@. STPRNT  D1,D2,SP.     NH
)@@G@@      'STRING PRINT'                       JC00             @I@@@@.     NI
)@@G@@                                                             JC00       NJ
)@@G@@      @I@@@@. THIS PRINTS THE STRING SP AS DESCRIBED BY D2, THE 'FILE CONK
)@@G@@NTROL  JC00             @I@@@@. BLOCK'. THE RELEVANT PARTS OF D2 ARE:   NL
)@@G@@                         JC00             @I@@@@.    A(A(D2)+D) = FILE UNM
)@@G@@NIT NUMBER.                                JC00             @I@@@@.    ANN
)@@G@@(A(D2)+2D) = POINTER TO FORMAT--A STRING IN STANDARD FORM.   JC00       NO
)@@G@@      @I@@@@.                                                           NP
)@@G@@       JC00             @I@@@@. D1 IS CURRENTLY NOT IN USE.             NQ
)@@G@@                         JC00             @I@@@@. THE FORTRAN ROUTINES TNR
)@@G@@HAT ARE CALLED ARE:                        JC00             @I@@@@.    NNS
)@@G@@WDU$                                                         JC00       NT
)@@G@@      @I@@@@.    NIO1$                                                  NU
)@@G@@       JC00             @I@@@@.    NIO2$                                NV
)@@G@@                         JC00             @I@@@@. SOME DOCUMENTATION ON NW
)@@G@@HOW THESE WORK SHOULD BE FOUND AND         JC00             @I@@@@. INCLNX
)@@G@@UDED HERE AS SOON AS PRACTICAL.                              JC00       NY
)@@G@@      @I@@@@.                                                           NZ
)@@G@@       JC00             @I@@@@. THIS WILL APPARENTLY WORK FOR > 64K, UNLOA
)@@G@@ESS THERE ARE ADDRESS    JC00             @I@@@@. RESTRICTIONS IN THE FOOB
)@@G@@RTRAN I/O ROUTINES.                        JC00             @I@@@@.     OC
)@@G@@                                                             JC00       OD
)@@G@@      @I@@@@. DON'T CURRENTLY KNOW EXACTLY WHICH REGISTERS ARE USED, SINOE
)@@G@@CE     JC00             @I@@@@. CALLS ARE MADE ON LIBRARY ROUTINES FOR WOF
)@@G@@HICH THIS INFO ISN'T KNOWJC00             @I@@@@.                       OG
)@@G@@                                           JC00             @I@@@@STPRNTOH

)@@G@@                                                             JC05 @I[@@@OX

)@@G@@                                                @I@@@@          AX,H2   PB

)@@G@@                              @I@@@@          DSA       A7,36.          PK
)@@G@@                                                @I@@@@          DI,U    PL
)@@G@@  A7,6.                                                           @I@@@@PM
)@@G@@          AA,U      A8,',A0'.                                           PN
)@@G@@            @I@@@@          SA,H1     A8,FORMAT+1.                      PO
)@@G@@                              @I@@@@          DSA       A7,36.          PP
)@@G@@                                                @I@@@@          DI,U    PQ

)@@G@@            @I@@@@          LSSL      A7,18.                            PT

)@@G@@                                                @I@@@@          +       QK

)@@G@@*****************************************SUBTRT**JC00             @I@[@@SY
)@@G@@INT**     PROC      1.                                                  SZ
)@@G@@            @I@[@@SUBTRT**  NAME      015.               SUBTRACT ADDRESTA
)@@G@@SES                           @I@[@@SUM**     NAME      014.            TB
)@@G@@   SUM ADDRESSES                                @I@[@@OV        EQU     TC
)@@G@@  INT(1,*4).                                                      @I@[@@TD
)@@G@@OK        EQU       INT(1,*5).                                          TE
)@@G@@            @I@[@@          DL        A0,INT(1,2).                      TF
)@@G@@                              @I@[@@          I$        INT(0,0),0,0,0,0TG
)@@G@@,INT(1,3)                                       @I@[@@  DO 1-OV ,    JO TH
)@@G@@  INT(1,4).      IF FAIL EXIT, JUMP ON OVERFLOW  JC05             @I@[@@TI
)@@G@@          DS        A0,INT(1,1).                                        TJ
)@@G@@            @I@[@@  DO 1-OK ,    JNO  INT(1,5).      IF SUCCESS EXIT, JUTK
)@@G@@MP ON NO OVERJC05             @I@[@@          END.                      TL
)@@G@@                                                @I@[@@. ****************TM
)@@G@@*****************************************SUBTRT**JC00             @G@@@[TN
)@@G@@. *********************************************************SUBTRT**JC13*TO
)@@G@@@G@@@[. SUBTRT  D1,D2,D3,FAIL,SUCC.      'SUBTRACT INTEGERS'            TP
)@@G@@ JC13*@G@@@[.                                                           TQ
)@@G@@       JC13*@G@@@[. A(D1) := A(D2) - A(D3); FV(D1) := FV(D2)            TR
)@@G@@             JC13*@G@@@[.                                               TS
)@@G@@                   JC13*@G@@@[. A0-A1 USED.                             TT
)@@G@@                         JC13*@G@@@[.                                   TU
)@@G@@                               JC13 @G@@@[SUBTRT**  PROC      1.        TV
)@@G@@                                     JC13 @G@@@[ .                      TW
)@@G@@                                            JC13@G@@@[SE        EQU     TX
)@@G@@  1-SUBTRT(1,*5).     SUCCESS EXIT EXISTS.       JC13 @G@@@[.           TY
)@@G@@                                                       JC13 @G@@@[      TZ
)@@G@@    DL        A0,SUBTRT(1,2).     LOAD D2.                   JC13 @G@@@[UA
)@@G@@          ANA       A0,SUBTRT(1,3).     - A(D3)                    JC13 UB
)@@G@@@G@@@[          JO        FAIL.               TEST FOR OVERFLOW.        UC
)@@G@@ JC13 @G@@@[          DS        A0,SUBTRT(1,1).     TO D1.              UD
)@@G@@       JC13 @G@@@[ DO SE ,  J         SUBTRT(1,5).        TAKE SUCCESS EUE
)@@G@@XIT.         JC13 @G@@@[.                                               UF
)@@G@@                   JC13 @G@@@[FAIL      LOCC      SUBTRT(1,4),$.      DEUG
)@@G@@FINE FAILURE EXIT.       JC13 @G@@@[          END.      SUBTRT.         UH
)@@G@@                               JC13 @G@@@[. ****************************UI
)@@G@@*****************************SUBTRT**JC13*@G@@@[. **********************UJ
)@@G@@***********************************SUM*****JC13*@G@@@[. SUM  D1,D2,D3,FAUK
)@@G@@IL,SUCC.         'SUM INTEGERS'                  JC13 @G@@@[.           UL
)@@G@@                                                       JC13 @G@@@[. A(D1UM
)@@G@@) := A(D2) + A(D3); FV(D1) := FV(D2)                         JC13 @G@@@[UN
)@@G@@.                                                                  JC13 UO
)@@G@@@G@@@[. A0-A1 USED.                                                     UP
)@@G@@ JC13 @G@@@[.                                                           UQ
)@@G@@       JC13 @G@@@[SUM**     PROC      1.                                UR
)@@G@@             JC13 @G@@@[.                                               US
)@@G@@                   JC13 @G@@@[SE        EQU       1-SUM(1,*5).   SUCCESSUT
)@@G@@ EXIT EXISTS.            JC13 @G@@@[.                                   UU
)@@G@@                               JC13 @G@@@[          DL        A0,SUM(1,2UV
)@@G@@).   LOAD D2.                        JC13 @G@@@[          AA        A0,SUW
)@@G@@UM(1,3).   + A(D3).                        JC13 @G@@@[          JO      UX
)@@G@@  FAIL.          TEST FOR OVERFLOW.              JC13 @G@@@[          DSUY
)@@G@@        A0,SUM(1,1).   TO D1.                          JC13 @G@@@[ DO SEUZ
)@@G@@ ,  J         SUM(1,5).      TAKE SUCCESS EXIT IF IT EXISTS  JC13 @G@@@[VA
)@@G@@.                                                                  JC13 VB
)@@G@@@G@@@[FAIL      LOCC      SUM(1,4),$.                                   VC
)@@G@@ JC13 @G@@@[          END.      SUM.                                    VD
)@@G@@       JC13 @G@@@[. ****************************************************VE
)@@G@@*****SUM*****JC13*@I@@@@. **********************************************VF
)@@G@@***********SYNVEC**JC00             @I@@@@SYNVEC**  PROC      1,1.      VG
)@@G@@ENTRY IN SYNTAX TABLE VECTOR.        JC30             @I@@@@ACTION    EQVH
)@@G@@U       SYNVEC(1,1).   ACTION TO TAKE FOR CHAR:        JC30             VI
)@@G@@@I@@@@.                                  IF CONTIN OR GOTO, NAME OF TABLVJ
)@@G@@EJC30             @I@@@@.                                  IF TAG, '*' FVK
)@@G@@OLLOWED BY TAG.    JC30             @I@@@@PUT       EQU       SYNVEC(1,2VL
)@@G@@).   IF NON-ZERO, VALUE TO RETURN.   JC30             @I@@@@.           VM
)@@G@@                                                       JC30             VN
)@@G@@@I@@@@ DO SYNVEC(1,*1) ,   +   ACTION,PUT.             IF TAG.          VO
)@@G@@ JC30             @I@@@@ DO 1-SYNVEC(1,*1) , +   ACTION-TABLES,PUT.     VP
)@@G@@ TABLE ADDRESS.    JC30             @I@@@@.                             VQ
)@@G@@                                     JC30             @I@@@@          ENVR
)@@G@@D.      SYNVEC.                                        JC30             VS
)@@G@@@I@@@@. *********************************************************SYNVEC*VT
)@@G@@*JC00             @I@@@@. **********************************************VU
)@@G@@***********TESTF***JC07             @I@@@@. TESTF  DE,FL,FAIL,SUCC.     VV
)@@G@@'TEST FLAG'                          JC07             @I@@@@.           VW
)@@G@@                                                       JC07             VX
)@@G@@@I@@@@. F(DE) IF TESTED TO SEE IF THE FLAG FL IS SET.  IF IT IS, TRANSFEVY
)@@G@@RJC07             @I@@@@. IS TO SUCC; IF NOT, IT IS TO FAIL.  FL MUST BEVZ
)@@G@@ A POWER OF 2 TO WOJC07             @I@@@@. CORRECTLY; ONLY THE LAST 16 WA
)@@G@@BITS ARE SIGNIFICANT.  IF FL=0, THE  JC07             @I@@@@. FAILURE EXWB
)@@G@@IT WILL BE TAKEN, THOUGH THIS ISN'T REQUIRED BY THE    JC07             WC
)@@G@@@I@@@@. DEFINITION OF THE MACRO.                                        WD
)@@G@@ JC07             @I@@@@.                                               WE
)@@G@@                   JC07             @I@@@@. A0 IS USED.                 WF
)@@G@@                                     JC07             @I@@@@.           WG
)@@G@@                                                       JC07             WH
)@@G@@@I@@@@TESTF**   PROC      1.                  (3-4 WORDS GENERATED.)    WI
)@@G@@ JC07             @I@@@@FE        EQU       1-TESTF(1,*3).      FAILURE WJ
)@@G@@EXIT EXISTS.       JC07             @I@@@@SE        EQU       1-TESTF(1,WK
)@@G@@*4).      SUCCESS EXIT EXISTS.       JC07             @I@@@@.           WL
)@@G@@                                                       JC07             WM
)@@G@@@I@@@@          LA,H1     A0,TESTF(1,1)+1.    F(DE).                    WN
)@@G@@ JC07             @I@@@@ DO FE ,  TOP,U     A0,TESTF(1,2).      PARITY OWO
)@@G@@DD IF FLAG EXISTS  JC07             @I@@@@ DO 1-FE ,  TEP,U   A0,TESTF(1WP
)@@G@@,2).      EVEN IF NOT.               JC07             @I@@@@ DO FE ,  J WQ
)@@G@@        TESTF(1,3).         FAIL EXIT, IF NEEDED       JC07             WR
)@@G@@@I@@@@ DO SE ,  J         TESTF(1,4).    SUCCESS EXIT.                  WS
)@@G@@ JC07             @I@]@@          LOFF.                                 WT
)@@G@@                   JC07             @I[@@@          END.                WU
)@@G@@                                     JC07             @I@@@@. **********WV
)@@G@@***********************************************TESTF***JC07             WW
)@@G@@@I@@@@. *********************************************************TESTFI*WX
)@@G@@*JC07             @I@@@@. TESTFI  DE,FL,FAIL,SUCC.         ' TEST FLAG IWY
)@@G@@NDIRECT'           JC07             @I@@@@.                             WZ
)@@G@@                                     JC07             @I@@@@. THIS TESTSXA
)@@G@@ F(A(DE)) FOR THE FLAG FL, AND BRANCHES TO SUCC IF IT  JC07             XB
)@@G@@@I@@@@. IS FOUND, AND TO FAIL IF NOT.  LIKE FOR TESTF, FL MUST BE A POWEXC
)@@G@@RJC07             @I@@@@. OF 2, AND ONLY THE LAST 16 BITS ARE SIGNIFICANXD
)@@G@@T.                 JC07             @I@@@@.                             XE
)@@G@@                                     JC07             @I@@@@. A0 USED.  XF
)@@G@@                                                       JC07             XG
)@@G@@@I@@@@.                                                                 XH
)@@G@@ JC07             @I@@@@TESTFI**  PROC      1.                  (4-5 WORXI
)@@G@@DS GENERATED.)     JC07             @I@@@@FE        EQU       1-TESTFI(1XJ
)@@G@@,*3).     FAILURE EXIT EXISTS.       JC07             @I@@@@SE        EQXK
)@@G@@U       1-TESTFI(1,*4).     SUCCESS EXIT EXISTS.       JC07             XL
)@@G@@@I@@@@.                                                                 XM
)@@G@@ JC07             @I@@@@          LA        A0,TESTFI(1,1).     A(DE)   XN
)@@G@@                   JC07             @I@@@@          LA,H1     A0,1,A0.  XO
)@@G@@          F(A(DE)).                  JC07             @I@@@@ DO FE ,   TXP
)@@G@@OP,U    A0,TESTFI(1,2).     ODD PARITY IF FLAG EXISTS  JC07             XQ
)@@G@@@I@@@@ DO 1-FE , TEP,U    A0,TESTFI(1,2).     EVEN IF NOT.              XR
)@@G@@ JC07             @I@@@@ DO FE ,  J         TESTFI(1,3).        FAIL EXIXS
)@@G@@T, IF NEEDED.      JC07             @I@@@@ DO SE ,  J         TESTFI(1,4XT
)@@G@@).        SUCCESS EXIT.              JC07             @I@]@@          LOXU
)@@G@@FF.                                                    JC07             XV
)@@G@@@I[@@@          END.                                                    XW
)@@G@@ JC07             @I@@@@. **********************************************XX

)@@G@@***********TITLE***JC30             @I@@@@. ****************************YD
)@@G@@*****************************TOP*****JC03             @I@@@@. TOPBLK  D1YE
)@@G@@,D2,D3.                'FIND TOP OF BLOCK'             JC30             YF
)@@G@@@I@@@@.                                                                 YG
)@@G@@ JC00             @I@@@@. THIS SCANS BACKWARDS FOR THE 'TOP' OF A BLOCK YH
)@@G@@OF MEMORY.  ITS    JC00             @I@@@@. NAME IS DIFFERENT FROM THE SYI
)@@G@@TANDARD SNOBOL4 MACRO DUE TO CONFLICTJC00             @I@@@@. WITH THE 1YJ
)@@G@@108 'TOP' COMMAND (WHICH IS USED BY THIS MACRO).       JC00             YK
)@@G@@@I@@@@. A BLOCK STARTS WITH A DESCRIPTOR WITH THE TTL FLAG SET.  A(D3)  YL
)@@G@@ JC00             @I@@@@. GIVES THE ADDRESS OF THE LAST WORD OF THE BLOCYM
)@@G@@K; SCANNING STARTS JC00             @I@@@@. WITH THIS DESCR (WHICH MAY BYN
)@@G@@E A TTL) AND EACH PRECEDING DESCR    JC00             @I@@@@. IS EXAMINEYO
)@@G@@D UNTIL A TTL FLAG IS FOUND.  A(D1) IS THEN SET TO THE JC00             YP
)@@G@@@I@@@@. ADDRESS OF THE START OF THE BLOCK, AND A(D2) IS SET TO A(D3)-A(DYQ
)@@G@@1JC00             @I@@@@. THE SIZE IN WORDS OF THE BLOCK.  FV(D1) IS SETYR
)@@G@@ TO FV(D3); FV(D2) JC00             @I@@@@. IS SET TO 0.                YS
)@@G@@                                     JC00             @I@@@@.           YT
)@@G@@                                                       JC00             YU
)@@G@@@I@@@@. THIS SHOULD WORK FOR > 64K.                                     YV
)@@G@@ JC00             @I@@@@. A0-A1 USED.                                   YW
)@@G@@                   JC00             @I@@@@.                             YX
)@@G@@                                     JC00             @I@@@@TOPBLK**  PRYY
)@@G@@OC      1,10.                                          JC30             YZ
)@@G@@@I@@@@          DL        A0,TOPBLK(1,3).     STARTING ADDRESS.         ZA
)@@G@@ JC30             @I@@@@          LXI,U     A0,-2.                      ZB
)@@G@@                                    @I@@@@          LA,U      A2,TTL.   ZC
)@@G@@                                                      @I@@@@          TOZD
)@@G@@P,H1    A2,1,*A0.                                                       ZE
)@@G@@@I@@@@          J         $-1.                                          ZF
)@@G@@                  @I@@@@          AH        A0,(2,2).                   ZG
)@@G@@                                    @I@@@@          DS        A0,TOPBLK(ZH
)@@G@@1,1).     D1 = START OF BLOCK.       JC30             @I@@@@          ANZI
)@@G@@A       A0,TOPBLK(1,3).     SIZE OF BLOCK              JC30             ZJ
)@@G@@@I@@@@          SMA       A0,TOPBLK(1,2).     GOES TO A(D2).            ZK
)@@G@@ JC30             @I@@@@          SZ        TOPBLK(1,2)+1.      FV(D2) =ZL
)@@G@@ 0.                JC30             @I@@@@          END.                ZM
)@@G@@                                                      @I@@@@. **********ZN

)@@G@@@I@@@@. *********************************************************TRIMSP*ZP
)@@G@@*JC03             @I@@@@. TRIMSP  S1,S2.              'TRIM SPECIFIER'  ZQ
)@@G@@                   JC00             @I@@@@.                             ZR
)@@G@@                                     JC00             @I@@@@. THIS COPIEZS
)@@G@@S THE AFVO-FIELDS OF S2 TO S1, BUT L(S2) IS ADJUSTED SOJC00             ZT
)@@G@@@I@@@@. TO EXCLUDE ANY TRAILING BLANKS.  THUS L(S1) <= L(S2), AND S1 IS ZU
)@@G@@AJC00             @I@@@@. INITIAL SUBSTRING OF S2.  THERE IS LITTLE POINZV
)@@G@@T IN RE-WRITING THIJC00             @I@@@@. AS A SUBROUTINE, SINCE IT ISZW
)@@G@@ ONLY USED TWICE.                    JC00             @I@@@@.           ZX
)@@G@@                                                       JC00             ZY
)@@G@@@I@@@@. THIS SHOULD WORK FOR > 64K.                                     ZZ
)@@G@@ JC00             @I@@@@. X1, A0-A3, A15 USED.                          AA
)@@G@@                   JC00             @I@@@@.                             AB
)@@G@@                                     JC00             @I@@@@TRIMSP**  PRAC

)@@G@@*****************************VCMPIC**JC07             @I@@@@. VCMPIC  D1CZ
)@@G@@,N,D2,GT,EQ,LT.   'VALUE COMP INDIRECT WITH OFFSET CONSJC07             DA
)@@G@@@I@@@@.                                                                 DB
)@@G@@ JC07             @I@@@@. IF V(A(D1)+N)  >  V(D2)  THEN GO TO GT;       DC
)@@G@@                   JC07             @I@@@@. IF V(A(D1)+N)  =  V(D2)  THEDD
)@@G@@N GO TO EQ;                          JC07             @I@@@@. IF V(A(D1)DE
)@@G@@+N)  <  V(D2)  THEN GO TO LT;                          JC07             DF
)@@G@@@I@@@@.                                                                 DG
)@@G@@ JC07             @I@@@@. N MUST BE < 65536.  SEE ACOMP FOR MORE COMMENTDH
)@@G@@S.                 JC07             @I@@@@. A0 USED.                    DI
)@@G@@                                     JC07             @I@@@@.           DJ
)@@G@@                                                       JC07             DK
)@@G@@@I@@@@VCMPIC**  PROC      1.                                            DL
)@@G@@ JC07             @I@@@@GTE       EQU       1-VCMPIC(1,*4).     GT EXISTDM
)@@G@@S.                 JC07             @I@@@@LTE       EQU       1-VCMPIC(1DN
)@@G@@,*6).     LT EXISTS.                 JC07             @I@@@@.           DO
)@@G@@                                                       JC07             DP
)@@G@@@I@@@@          LA        A0,VCMPIC(1,1).     A(D1)                     DQ
)@@G@@ JC07             @I@@@@          LA,H2     A0,VCMPIC(1,2)+1,A0.     V(NDR
)@@G@@+A(D1)).           JC07             @I@@@@          ANA,H2    A0,VCMPIC(DS
)@@G@@1,3)+1.   SUB V(D2).                 JC07             @G@@@[          JODT
)@@G@@        AERROR.             CHECK FOR OVERFLOW         JC12 @I@@@@.     DU
)@@G@@                                                             JC07       DV
)@@G@@      @I@@@@          JZ        A0,EQ.              EQ EXIT--ALWAYS NEEDDW
)@@G@@ED.    JC07             @I@@@@ DO GTE , JP        A0,VCMPIC(1,4).     GTDX
)@@G@@ EXIT.                   JC07             @I@@@@ DO LTE , JN        A0,VDY
)@@G@@CMPIC(1,6).     LT EXIT.                   JC07             @I@@@@.     DZ
)@@G@@                                                             JC07       EA
)@@G@@      @I@@@@EQ        LOCC      VCMPIC(1,5),$.      EQ EXIT HERE IF OMITEB
)@@G@@TED.   JC07             @I@]@@          LOFF.                           EC
)@@G@@                         JC07             @I[@@@          END.          ED
)@@G@@                                           JC07             @I@@@@. ****EE

)@@G@@      @G@@@[. *********************************************************VEG
)@@G@@EQL****JC13*@G@@@[. VEQL  D1,D2,NE,EQ.               'ADDRESS EQUALITY TEH
)@@G@@EST'         JC13 @G@@@[.                                               EI
)@@G@@                   JC13 @G@@@[. IF V(D1) = V(D2) THEN GO TO EQ ELSE GO TEJ
)@@G@@O NE.                    JC13 @G@@@[. EITHER EXIT MAY BE OMITTED.       EK
)@@G@@                               JC13 @G@@@[. SEE ACOMP FOR SOME PERTINENTEL
)@@G@@ COMMENTS.                           JC13 @G@@@[.                       EM

)@@G@@       JC13 @G@@@[.                                                     EU

)@@G@@                   JC13 @G@@@[          ANA,H2    A0,VEQL(1,2)+1.     - EW
)@@G@@V(D2).                   JC13 @G@@@[ DO NEE , JNZ       A0,VEQL(1,3).  NEX
)@@G@@E EXIT.                        JC13 @G@@@[ DO EQE , JZ        A0,VEQL(1,EY
)@@G@@4).  EQ EXIT.                        JC13 @G@@@[          END.      VEQLEZ

)@@G@@. *********************************************************INVOKE**JC21 JL
)@@G@@@G@@@@.      RCALL  X,INVOKE Y FAIL,NRET,VRET.                          JM
)@@G@@ JC21 @G@@@@.                                                           JN
)@@G@@       JC21 @G@@@@. THIS INVOKES THE INTERPRETER FUNCTION DESCRIBED BY YJO
)@@G@@ AS FOLLOWS: JC21 @G@@@@.      A(Y) = THE FUNCTION, A LOCATION IN FTABLEJP
)@@G@@.                  JC21 @G@@@@.      V(Y) = THE NUMBER OF PARAMETERS IN JQ
)@@G@@THE CODE STREAM.         JC21 @G@@@@.      F(Y) HAS THE 'FNC' FLAG SET. JR
)@@G@@                               JC21 @G@@@@. THE VALUE RETURNED WILL BE AJS
)@@G@@SSIGNED TO X.  IF THE VALUE IS NAMED,JC21 @G@@@@. X WILL POINT TO ITS NAJT

)@@G@@LUE OF 0/0/0 TO BE RETURNED, BUT THIS MAY NOT ALWAYS BE TRUE.JC21 @G@@@@JX

)@@G@@*****ASSIGN**JC00 @G@@@@.      ASSIGN(N,V)  OR  N = V                   VM

)@@G@@                         JC00 @G@@@@. EITHER OF THESE CALLS THIS CODE, WVO
)@@G@@HICH CAUSES N TO TAKE ON THE   JC00 @G@@@@. VALUE OF V.  N MUST BE NAMEDVP
)@@G@@, OF COURSE, OR AN ERROR WILL OCCUR. JC00 @G@@@@. IF THERE ARE MORE THANVQ
)@@G@@ 2 ARGUMENTS, THE REST WILL BE EVALUATED   JC00 @G@@@@. (BEFORE THE ASSIVR
)@@G@@GNMENT) AND IGNORED.  THE VALUE OF V IS RETURNED.JC00 @G@@@@.           VS
